 Progress: 1st +360, 2nd +180, 3rd +130, 4th +80\n3-player Silver Chest Progress: 1st +240, 2nd +135, 3rd +50\n4-player Bond Point Bonus: 60\n3-player Bond Point Bonus: 40\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity","Rank Limit: Expert - Master\n\n4-player Order Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +5, 3rd -5, 4th -15\n3-player Order Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +0, 3rd -15\n\n\nEast Round Match:\n\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\n\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\n\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\n\n4-player Rank Bonus: 1st +40, 2nd +20, 3rd +0, 4th - penalty based on current rank\n3-player Rank Bonus: 1st +55, 2nd +0, 3rd - penalty based on current rank\n4-player Gold Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60\n3-player Gold Chest Progress: 1st +170, 2nd +100, 3rd +40\n4-player Bond Point Bonus: 40\n3-player Bond Point Bonus: 25\n\nSouth Round Match:\n\nEntry Limit: 7000 Coppers\n\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 140 Coppers\n\nEntry Fee: 1400 Coppers\n\n4-player Rank Bonus: 1st +80, 2nd +40, 3rd +0, 4th - penalty based on current rank\n3-player Rank Bonus: 1st +105, 2nd 0, 3rd - penalty based on current rank\n4-player Gold Chest Progress: 1st +360, 2nd +180, 3rd +130, 4th +80\n3-player Gold Chest Progress: 1st +240, 2nd +135, 3rd +50\n4-player Bond Point Bonus: 60\n3-player Bond Point Bonus: 40\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","Rank Limit: Master - Saint\n\n4-player Order Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +5, 3rd -5, 4th -15\n3-player Order Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +0, 3rd -15\n\n\nEast Round Match:\n\nEntry Limit: 10000 Coppers\n\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 200 Coppers\n\nEntry Fee: 2000 Coppers\n\n4-player Rank Bonus: 1st +55, 2nd +30, 3rd +0, 4th - penalty based on current rank\n3-player Rank Bonus: 1st +75, 2nd +0, 3rd - penalty based on current rank\n4-player Jade Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60\n3-player Jade Chest Progress: 1st +160, 2nd +100, 3rd +40\n4-player Bond Point Bonus: 40\n3-player Bond Point Bonus: 25\n\nSouth Round Match:\n\nEntry Limit: 14000 Coppers\n\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 280 Coppers\n\nEntry Fee: 2800 Coppers\n\n4-player Rank Bonus: 1st +110, 2nd +55, 3rd +0, 4th - penalty based on current rank\n3-player Rank Bonus: 1st +160, 2nd 0, 3rd - penalty based on current rank\n4-player Jade Chest Progress: 1st +360, 2nd +180, 3rd +130, 4th +80\n3-player Jade Chest Progress: 1st +240, 2nd +135, 3rd +50\n4-player Bond Point Bonus: 60\n3-player Bond Point Bonus: 40\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","Mode:\n4-Player: 4-Player Mahjong rules used\n3-Player: 3-Player Mahjong rules used\nLength:\nVS AI: Practice with AI, only play 1 East Game\nEast Wind Match: Play an East Wind round with other players or AI\nTwo-Wind Match: Play a Two-Wind Match with other players or AI\nIn Friends Room, only game points are calculated. Rank Points and coppers will not be affected.","Enter a room number, or tap the invitation link sent by a friend to join the corresponding room and start playing!\nIn Friends Room, only game points are calculated. Rank Points and coppers will not be affected.","Rank Limit: N/A\nMinimum coppers: N/A\nMaximum coppers: N/A\nRank Points: N/A\n\nMatches played in Smash Room will involve no coppers or Rank Points. There will be no entry restrictions either. All players can enjoy Mahjong here!","You have a poor connection. Please check your network proxy settings and try again.","Failed to connect to server","Attempting to connect to server. Please try again later.","Oops, something is wrong with the program. Please refresh and enter the game again.","An error occurred while loading to spectate the match. Please exit and re-enter again.","This match has ended. Leaving spectate mode.","This player has disabled messenger.","This player only allows friends to leave messages","Do you wish to delete this message?","You cannot send messages while in a match","Do you wish to leave this room?","Do you wish to close the game?","You cannot change so frequently. Please wait 30 seconds before trying again.","Starting Points: 35,000\nExtension into South: At the end of 3rd East game, if 1st place has less than 40,000 points\nLength: East Round Match\nRed Five: 2\nOpen Tanyao: On\nTsumo Loss： On\nWaiting Time: 5+20\n\n - 8 Dead Wall tiles;\n\n - 2,3,4,5,6,7,8-Man tiles are not used;\n\n - “Chii” is not allowed;\n\n - “North Wind” can be melded and used as a Kita Dora. Upon calling Kita, the player can draw an extra tile from the Dead Wall.\n\n - “Tsumo” after Kita is considered a Dead Wall Draw;\n\n - Kita is considered as a call (which disables Ippatsu/Miracle (Non-Dealer)/Nine Terminal Initial Draw/Double Riichi) but does not make Menzenchin invalid;\n\n - Players can declare a Ron when others are Kita, but this has no Yaku;\n\n - North Wind triplets are not considered as Yaku;","Starting Points: 35,000\nExtension into West: At the end of 3rd South game, if 1st place has less than 40,000 points\nLength: Two-Wind Match\nRed Five: 2\nOpen Tanyao: On\nTsumo Loss： On\nWaiting Time: 5+20\n\n - 8 Dead Wall tiles;\n\n - 2,3,4,5,6,7,8-Man tiles are not used;\n\n - “Chii” is not allowed;\n\n - “North Wind” can be melded and used as a Kita Dora. Upon calling Kita, the player can draw an extra tile from the Dead Wall.\n\n - “Tsumo” after Kita is considered a Dead Wall Draw;\n\n - Kita is considered as a call (which disables Ippatsu/Miracle (Non-Dealer)/Nine Terminal Initial Draw/Double Riichi) but does not make Menzenchin invalid;\n\n - Players can declare a Ron when others are Kita, but this has no Yaku;\n\n - North Wind triplets are not considered as Yaku;","ATK: This stat increases with your average points won in the last 100 games;\n\nDEF: This stat increases as your deal-in rate over the last 100 games decreases;\n\nSPD: This stat increases as your win rate over the last 100 games increases;\n\nLUK: This stat is higher when you had more Dora-Yaku (Dora, Ura Dora, Red Five & Ippatsu) in the last 20 wins.","You have been removed from the room","Tips include: \nSame Tile: When you select a tile, similar tiles in the discard pile will be highlighted \nTenpai: Display the type and remaining quantity of tiles required to win when you achieve Tenpai \nDora: Dora tiles will be highlighted.","Open Tanyao: \nWhen “Open Tanyao” is on, “Tanyao” also counts as a Yaku when you have called for tiles \nWhen “Open Tanyao” is off, “Tanyao” only counts as a Yaku when you have Menzenchin (no calls made).","Players can get 1 Faith each time they summon. \nClick the button on the left to enter Faith Shop. Rare items and characters can be purchased with Faith.","In the tournament lobby, players can create and manage different tournaments using customized rules. \n Illegal activities, such as gambling, are strictly prohibited in Mahjong Soul and will face serious consequences once found. We hope all players can work together to ensure a healthy gaming environment. \n\nParticipant:\n - Tournament matches will not involve coppers or PTs. \n - Tournament match results will not be reflected in “Recent Trends”, “Style (stats)” or “Match Info”, but may appear in “Recent High Score”. \n - Players can only prepare for tournaments marked as “In Progress”. \n - Tournament matches can only be spectated in corresponding tournament rooms with a 300 seconds delay. \n - Participants can view the match logs of a tournament within the tournament room. \n\nOrganizer:\n - Organizers can enter the organizer center to create and manage tournaments via “Manage Tournament” on mahjongsoul.yo-star.com. \n - Creating a tournament will cost 60 Jade. \n - A tournament room will exist for up to 90 days, starting from the day it was created. \n - Tournament matches will use the same rules as the standard Ranked Match if “Advanced Rules” are disabled. \n - Creators can add other players as admins to help manage the tournament. \n - Tournament admins may use statistical tools in the organizer center to analyze participant scores and rankings. \n - Tournament matches must be manually activated by admins. Participants will not be randomly matched.","3-Player Mahjong Rules:\n - Order Bonus +15, 0, -15\n - 8 Dead Wall tiles\n - 2M-8M tiles not used\n - “Chii” is not allowed\n -“North Wind” can be melded and used as a Kita Dora. Upon calling Kita, the player can draw an extra tile from the Dead Wall.\n - “Tsumo” after Kita is considered a Dead Wall Draw\n - Kita is considered as a call (which disables Ippatsu/Miracle (Non-Dealer)/Nine Terminal Initial Draw/Double Riichi) but does not make Menzenchin invalid\n - Players can declare a Ron when others are Kita, but this has no Yaku\n - North Winds are considered as Useless Wind when in triplets\n - You may turn “Tsumo Loss” on or off in the advanced settings.","Cannot find match list. Please refresh and try again.","Failed to connect to match server. Please refresh and try again.","Match server list is empty. Unable to connect.","You have a poor connection. Please check your network proxy settings and try again.","Poor network connection. Please use VPN or switch your internet environment.","“Tsumo Loss” is a rule that disregards the points that should be paid by the North player in a 3-Player Mahjong match. The points will still be calculated like a Tsumo game for 4-Player Mahjong. This makes the points won from Tsumo in a 3-Player game 1/3 or 1/4 lower than from the points won from Ron. \nIf “Tsumo Loss” is turned off, the points that should be paid by the North player will be evenly distributed to the other two players. In this way, games won from both Tsumo and Ron will receive the same points.","Rank Limit: Saint and above\n\n4-player Order Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +5, 3rd -5, 4th -15\n3-player Order Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +0, 3rd -15\n\nIn Throne Room, Dora tips, same tile tips and Tenpai tips are disabled.\n\n\nEast Round Match:\n\nEntry Limit: 10000 Coppers\n\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 200 Coppers\n\nEntry Fee: 2000 Coppers\n\n4-player Rank Bonus: 1st +60, 2nd +30, 3rd +0, 4th - penalty based on current rank\n3-player Rank Bonus: 1st +120, 2nd +0, 3rd - penalty based on current rank\n4-player Throne Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60\n3-player Throne Chest Progress: 1st +170, 2nd +100, 3rd +40\n4-player Bond Point Bonus: 40\n3-player Bond Point Bonus: 25\n\n*In Celestial Rank, the Rank Points Bonus will be replaced by Soul Points Order Bonus:\n  4-Player: 1st +0.3, 2nd +0.1, 3rd -0.1, 4th -0.3\n  3-Player: 1st +0.3, 2nd +0, 3rd -0.3\n\n* If all players in a match are at Celestial Rank, then the Soul Point change will be doubled.\n\n\nSouth Round Match:\n\nEntry Limit: 14000 Coppers\n\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 280 Coppers\n\nEntry Fee: 2800 Coppers\n\n4-player Rank Bonus: 1st +120, 2nd +60, 3rd +0, 4th - penalty based on current rank\n3-player Rank Bonus: 1st +240, 2nd 0, 3rd - penalty based on current rank\n4-player Throne Chest Progress: 1st +360, 2nd +180, 3rd +130, 4th +80\n3-player Throne Chest Progress: 1st +240, 2nd +135, 3rd +50\n4-player Bond Point Bonus: 60\n3-player Bond Point Bonus: 40\n\n*In Celestial Rank, the Rank Points Bonus will be replaced by Soul Points Order Bonus:\n  4-Player: 1st +0.5, 2nd +0.2, 3rd -0.2, 4th -0.5\n  3-Player: 1st +0.5, 2nd +0, 3rd -0.5\n\n* If all players in a match are at Celestial Rank, then the Soul Point change will be doubled.\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","This route is busy. Please try another.","This route is unavailable. Please try another.","A better route is available. Switch now?","Under maintenance","Busy","Connection failed","Oops, you don\'t have enough coppers to enter this room. Please select a lower room level.","Oops, you cannot enter this room with your current rank. Please select a room appropriate to your rank.","Oops, you cannot enter this room with your current rank. Please select a room appropriate to your rank.","","Preparing tournament, stay tuned!","Your friends are on their way","Shop closed, more items are coming.","You cannot perform this action while in matchmaking","Deal-in is not the end; All Last is only the beginning!","No matter how big your hand is, a Tanyao will end it all.","You must have Yaku to declare a win. Before you make a call (Chii/Pon/Kan), make sure you check if you have Yaku.","Go to settings menu to view all types of Yaku","In settings, you can choose to play a tile with single or double click","Players who use IE or Opera browsers may encounter lag issues. We recommend Chrome，FireFox or Edge browsers.","You can now sort your favourite Jyanshis by using the mark function in the Dorm. There is also a toggle option that only display Jyanshis that are marked.","Four Concealed Triplets cannot be gained by winning with Ron, Seven Pairs won\'t be counted as Pure Double Sequence.","If you have any advice or need help with the game, go to [Settings] - [Others] - [Contact Us]","If you logged in with a social media account, you can go to [Setting] - [Others] and connect your account to an email address that hasn\'t been bound to a Yostar account before.","An account bound to email can log in on both the web version and the mobile version.","You can go to our official website (mahjongsoul.yo-star.com) to check out the manga, tournament information and other news.","Seven Pairs does not allow repeats in pairs, but Twice Pure Double Sequence does.","The probability of getting Blessing of Heaven in 4-Player Mahjong is 1 in 330,000.","When your point count is below 1000, you cannot declare Riichi.","Robbing a Closed Kan is only possible with Thirteen Orphans, other Yakus cannot do this.","There is a five minutes delay with streamed matches, so don\'t think about screen peeking.","Click on the star button in Log to add your favorite matches to your Collection.","After you change your name, there is a 30 day cooldown period before you can change it again.","Quest and Misc Shop will be refreshed every day at 5:00 A.M. (UTC-7).","3-Player Mahjong has no 2 to 8 Man tiles, so 1 Man and 9 Man are each other\'s Dora indicator.","When all players in a Ranked Match are at the Celestial rank, Final Showdown will be triggered.","An outfit can only be used after you get the corresponding character.","Mai Aihara is the priestess of the Temple of Moons, not Mahjong Soul Shrine.","Yui Yagi loves coffee, but she actually has a poor sense of taste.","Ichihime loves eating and napping, do you have similar interests?","However big your appetite is, you cannot Chii in 3-Player Mahjong.","Select your Riichi Bet style","Select the special effect when you win a hand","Select your specific effect when declaring Riichi","Select your hand style","Select the music played after you declare Riichi","Select a portrait frame","Select your Tile Call Indicator style","Tile Call Indicator","New update available for iOS. Please download from the official website.","Failed to retrieve version info. Please check your connection.","AI(Easy)","AI(Normal)","Failed to download log data","Connection error, please refresh and try again.","Auto Reconnect Failed","An error occurred when connecting to the Mahjong table","System under maintenance","Unknown","Game has already ended","Failed to retrieve reconnection information","Just now","minutes","hours","days","weeks","months","s","m","h","d","Friendly Match","Successfully used","Tournament Match","4-Player (1 Game)","4-Player East","4-Player South","4-Player (vs AI)","3-Player (1 Game)","3-Player East","3-Player South","3-Player (vs AI)","Cancel","Use","Do you wish to donate these gifts?","Donation Successful","Choose one to Chii","Choose one to Pon","Current version","Real name authentication: Completed","Real name authentication: Incomplete","Enter number","No Red Five","3 Red Five","4 Re