s will be converted into Star Stones","Chance to get gifts: 80%","You will get at least 1 purple gift when you perform a 10-time Summon.","Character Info","Height:","Birthday:","Age:","Blood Type:","CV:","Hobby:","Biography:","Voice","Sample 1","Sample 2","Sample 3","Remaining","Insufficient Summon Stones","Do you wish to spend","Jade","Purchase","Summon Stones?","Visit","Info","Voice","Effect","Emote","Bond","Requires a 5-heart Bond","Gift","Gift","Daily gift attempt:","Gift","Change Outfit","Event","Empty","Riichi Music","Invite","Add AI","Rules","Copy Link","Copy the room link and send it to your friends","Invite","Invited","In a match","There are no friends to invite","Starting in:","Exit","Yaku Type","Auto Arrange","A","Auto Call Win","R","No Chii/Pon/Kan","C","Auto Draw & Discard","D","Emote","Match End","Added to titles","Match paused. Please wait in patience","The system has detected you are AFK. Auto Draw & Discard enabled.","I\'m back","Mahjong Soul promises that all games are randomly generated. At the beginning of each match, the tile wall is already pre-determined, so the tiles issued in each game will not be changed, or influenced by any external factor. To support this statement, we have introduced a verification system. \n(The verification system used before May 23rd, 2023 is MD5, and after the maintenance on May 23rd, 2023 it has been upgraded to SHA-256 system.)\n\nEach tile has a unique code. \"Man\" tiles are represented by \"m\" (1m-9m), \"Pin\" tiles are represented by \"p\" (1p-9), \"Sou\" tiles are represented by \"s\" (1s-9s) and word tiles are represented by \"z\" (1z-7z, in the order of East, South, West, North, White, Green, and Red). For Red Fives: Red 5 Man is 0m, Red 5 Pin is 0p, Red 5 Sou is 0s. As such, each tile wall can be represented by a unique series of codes (tile wall code). \n\nFor SHA-256 verification after May 23rd, 2023:\n1. During the match, players can click the Dora Indicator on the top left corner to view and record the tile wall SHA-256 code. Each flush of tile wall generates one set of SHA-256 code.\n2. After a match, players can go to Log and verify the SHA-256 code in each game (recorded in the Log) against the value recorded when the game was played. The SHA-256 code obtained during the game should be consistent with the SHA-256 code in the Log. \n3. Enter the tile wall code in an SHA-256 generator and it will show the corresponding SHA-256 code. You can compare the SHA-256 code generated with the SHA-256 code provided in game.\n\nFor MD5 verification before May 23rd, 2023:\n1. During the match, players can click the Dora Indicator on the top left corner to view and record the tile wall MD5 code. Each flush of tile wall generates one set of MD5 code.\n2. After a match, players can go to Log and verify the MD5 code in each game (recorded in the Log) against the value recorded when the game was played. The MD5 code obtained during the game should be consistent with the MD5 code in the Log. \n3. Enter the tile wall code in an MD5 generator and it will show the corresponding MD5 code. You can compare the MD5 code generated with the MD5 code provided in game.","Show Hands","Deal-in Tile","","Turn","Wall","Repeat Counter","Exhaustive Draw","Wall Code:","Bond","Bond Gift","Furiten","Mangan at Draw","Deal-in","Please input the tournament name or ID.","Yostar Login","Login in other service ID","Remember me","Not enough Jade","Would you like to purchase some Jade?","Refresh in: {0}","You can change your name once every 30 days.","Verification failed","Verification failed, Info do not match","IP restricted","Device ID is banned","UID is banned","Tap to acquire a Verification Code","{0} Seconds","Failed to received Verification Code","Request is too frequent","Email address is Banned","Verification failed, the code is invalid or expired","Failed too many time, please try again later","Verification Code has been sent to your email, please use it before it is expired","Verification failed