ihime’s Gift Box Progress: 1st +360, 2nd +180, 3rd +130, 4th +80\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","Starting Points: 35,000\nExtension into South: At the end of 4th East game, if 1st place has less than 40,000 points\nLength: One-Wind Match\nRed Five: 3\nOpen Tanyao: On\nWaiting Time: 5+20","Clear current row to get bonus rewards","Clear current column to get bonus rewards","Clear all missions on board to get bonus rewards","Do you confirm to exit?","Portrait Frame","Outfit Voucher","Bind","Current Outfit Voucher status","Insufficient Outfit Voucher","Insufficient Outfit Voucher，Do you wish to Purchase ？","Premium:","Free:","This email is already linked to an existing Mahjong Soul account","Invalid email information","Account token error","Account settings","Bound","Shop","Google Pay needs the permission of reading external storage to complete the payment","Unlink successful","Unable to unlink the the last account","Failed to unlink, please try again","New updates detected, please try to restart your game","Account Binding","Not Bound","(Tap to bind)","(Tap to unbind)","You have reserved too many matches","Account Unbinding","Unbind Email:{0}","Unbind","Unbind Successfully","This email has not been bound with Yostar account","Failed to verify the email","Unable to unbind current account","Parameter error","(Tap to unbind)","","","","","Select your Tablecloth style","Select your Tile Back style","Select your Lobby background style","Save","This decoration theme is not saved. Do you still wish to continue?","Decoration","Character","Purchase in Shop","Donate gift","Duplicate characters will be converted to Wishing Stones.","Local Yaku","Special Rules: Open Hand Match Instructions\n\nAll players will show the tiles of their initial hands to the others. After discarding the first tile, the tiles drawn will not be shown anymore.\n\nGame Mode: Open Hand Match - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nOrder Bonus: 1st+15, 2nd+5, 3rd-5, 4th-15\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points=100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st+260, 2nd+130, 3rd+95, 4th+60\nBond Point Bonus: 40\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","GO","How to get","In Use","Change Outfit","Local Yaku","In Progress","View log","AFK Punishment Warning","AFK actions have been detected.\n\nSilver Chest & Bond Level & Quests Progress will not be counted in this match. If further AFK actions are detected, this account will be banned.","AFK Punishment Notice","Your account has been banned for your AFK actions until {0}. Please try to keep a quality game-play environment. Thank you for your understanding.","Match End","Last vote was not agreed by all the players, please start the next vote after 5 minutes.","Are you sure to vote to end the match?","(The match will end once all players agree.)","Agree","Disagree","Disagreed","Agreed","Special Rules: Chaotic Wall Break Instructions\n\n3 Dora indicators will be revealed at the beginning of the match. 5 Dora indicators can be revealed at most.\n\nOne player will receive the Wareme mark at the beginning of the match, and once this player has discarded 5 tiles in total, the Wareme mark will move to a random player (including the original holder).\n\nThe score of the marked player will be doubled after winning or losing (not including Riichi Bets and Round Bets).\n\nGame Mode: Chaotic Wall Break - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nOrder Bonus: 1st+15, 2nd+5, 3rd-5, 4th-15\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points=100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st+260, 2nd+130, 3rd+95, 4th+60\nBond Point Bonus: 40\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","Starting Points: 40,000\nExtension into South: At the end of 4th East game, if 1st place has less than 45,000 points\nLength: East Round Match\nRed Five: 3\nOpen Tanyao: On\nWaiting Time: 5+20","4/13 20:00 - \n4/22 13:59 (UTC-7)","Sign-in","Best continuous {0} games points","Best continuous {0} games ranks","Event Period: 2/26-3/7 13:59 (UTC-7) Current outing:","Next outing reward:","Story","To save the shrine, a mysterious priestess with cat ears has decided to start working for coppers.\nWhat fate awaits our naive Ichihime?\n\nEvent Period: 4/24 - 5/8 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nComplete daily quests (excluding games with AI) to get normal dice.\nComplete the specified number of laps on the event map to collect event rewards.\n\nUse the dice to accumulate experience to upgrade Ichihime\'s level!\nAll the level of Ichihime:\nCopper Hunter: no effect\nJunior Intern: Get +5% more copper on the map\nSenior Expert: Get +10% more copper on the map\nBest Employee: Get +30% more copper on the map\nLucky Cat: Get +50% more copper on the map\n\nMysterious chests are appearing on the map!\nItems that can be inside the mysterious chest: random number of copper, random sphere, Fortune Bag, Sage\'s Bag.\n\nAll the types of blocks:\nConvenience store: Get random number of copper when stopping on it.\nBecoming Community Volunteer: Get a random green gift when stopping on it.\nBoard game shop: Get a dice when stopping on it.\nMiki\'s jewelry shop: Get a random sphere when stopping on it.\nMahjong Soul bank: After using a dice or finish a lap on the map, copper will be deposited in the bank.\n-All the copper will be withdrew when stopping on Mahjong Soul bank.\nKaavi\'s fortune dial: Randomly select one of the following 6 effects.\n- Earn double coppers in the next move\n- Earn half coppers in the next move\n- Double the number of steps in the next move\n- Halve the number of steps in the next move\n- Move on 1 step\n- Refresh the location of mysterious chest","Freed Jyanshi","Earn double coppers in the next move","Earn half coppers in the next move","Double the number of steps in the next move","Halve the number of steps in the next move","Can be used in Dorm - Decoration","Copper on the map","Bond to unlock","","Jyanshi 1","Jyanshi 2","Jyanshi 3","Me","Anonymously Share","","Jyanshi 4","Get {0}","Working in a convenience store. Ichihime doesn\'t have a lot of energy...","Working in a convenience store. Ichihime is doing just fine.","Working in a convenience store. Ichihime has a lot of energy.","Working in a convenience store. Ichihime is feeling great!","Ichihime is doing community service. What a good kid!","Helping out in Miki\'s jewelry shop. You have been praised!","Working in a board game shop. Found a strange dice!","Arrived at Mahjong Soul Bank and withdrew all the deposit!","Opened a mysterious chest on the road. Wow, what\'s this...!","Share the log","Ichihime\'s ability has been activated!","Kaavi\'s Wheel of Fortune has been activated","Ichihime\'s ability \"Copper Hunter\" has been activated!","Ichihime\'s ability \"Junior Intern\" has been activated!","Ichihime\'s ability \"Senior Expert\" has been activated!","Ichihime\'s ability \"Best Employee\" has been activated!","Ichihime\'s ability \"Lucky Cat\" has been activated!","Ichihime\'s Working Adventure","Working Adventure Quest","Working adventure Rewards","Effect Display","Show Nickname","How to get","Anonymous","Real-time spectating","Back to log","SP Voice","Please search friends with friend ID.","If you have found any inappropriate information in the game, please contact our customer support.","Report","Report the nickname","We\'ve received your report. Thank you for your contribution in making a better gaming environment!","Reported successfully","Recently used","All","Error occurred when getting the report, please try again","Do you wish to quit and check your annual report?","Resummon","Expiry date:","Can be changed in the Settings","Limited-time title Expiry date:","300+0s","","","your email address:","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","Language","Change Language","Current Language:","简体中文","繁體中文","日本語","English","Invalid game log","","Narration","Choice","Switching over now...","Switch","Fullscreen","Screen Resolution","Path of Trial","Path of Trial Season One is started! \nEvent Period: 7/26 - 10/24 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7) duration: 90 Days\nMatch mode: 4-Player East\n\nDuring the event, click \"Start Challenge\" to start Path of Trial 4-Player East games.\nChallenge the Path of Trial by completing all the goals on the ticket within the specified number (Remaining Challenges: 5/5) of games. Once successful, your trial rank will increase and you will get the Goal Ticket reward.\nAchieve specified trial ranks to get rewards during the event (include limited title).\nDuring the event, you can get the weekly reward after playing 5 games in Path of Trial (reset every Sunday at 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)).\nTop 100 players will receive ranking rewards after Season 1 ends. (Expiry Date of the Portrait Frames: 2021/2/21 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7))\n\nTop 1 Player: Portrait Frame - Conqueror of Trials\nTop 2-10 Players: Portrait Frame - Master of Trials\nTop 11-100 Players: Portrait Frame - Expert of Trials\n\nWhen a challenge is in progress or has already failed, you can tap \"Re-publish\" to reset the progress and get a new Goal Ticket\nRe-publishing Goal Ticket will cost Coppers (first time in a day will be free; up to 5 times per day; The attempts will be refreshed everyday at 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7))\n\nEach time you Ron or complete a game in Path of Trial, you can get Trial Points based on the number of Hans you won or the final position\nWhen Trial Points are full, you can use the Stamp button.\nDuring a challenge, you can use the Stamp to mark an uncompleted goal as successfully completed.\nStamps cannot be used if the challenge is already successful or failed.\n\nMatch mode: Path of Trial - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 1500 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points=0 Copper\nEntry Fee: 1500 Copper\nMatches played in this mode are not ranked\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st+260, 2nd+130, 3rd+95, 4th+60","Would you like to use {0} Coppers to reset the progress and get a new Goal Ticket? You can re-publish the ticket {1} more time(s) today.","Please select a goal in progress and stamp \"Trial Succeeded\". Click the blank to cancel it.","Complete all the goals on this ticket to upgrade to Lv{0}.","Certified and published by Mahjong Soul Shrine. All rights reserved. Expiry Date: 2020/10/24 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7).","You have reached the max number of re-publishing today","","Click to continue","Friends\' Ranking","Ranking of Trial Rank","Receive the Trial Rank reward","The stamp is unavailble after finishing all the challenges on the ticket.","You have finished all the challenges on the ticket. Please click the \"Re-publish\" button to get new challenges.","You have finished all the challenges on the ticket and reach the limit of re-publishing. Please try tomorrow.","Weekly Reward","Remaining Challenges:","End game now?","Reward:","Trial Rank Description","Trial Points\n\nin the Path of Trial\nAchieve 1st place+16\nAchieve 2nd place+10\nAchieve 3rd place+6\nAchieve 4th place+3\nWinning(below Mangan)+1\nWinning(Mangan)+2\nWinning(Haneman)+3\nWinning(Baiman)+4\nWinning(Sanbaiman)+6\nWinning(Yakuman and above)+8\n\nWhen Trial Points are full, you can use the Stamp button.\nDuring a challenge, you can use the Stamp to mark an uncompleted goal as successfully completed.\nStamps cannot be used if the challenge is already successful or failed.","You cannot use \"Re-publish\" function during matchmaking.","Do you want to stop matchmaking and return to lobby?","Summer and beach! Miss Chiori\'s relaxing holiday has begun!\nWhile I was following her around, I noticed a girl in green that I seemed to have met somewhere...\n\nEvent period: 8/19 - 9/3 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nComplete daily [Relaxing Holiday Quest] to earn dices (excluding games vs. AI)\nGet Cool Ticket x3 each time when you pass the starting point on the event map (for the first 16 laps only\nCool Tickets can be used to redeem great rewards from [Is Keikumusume also an outdoor person?], such as Jyanshi \"Keikumusume\", Cool Summer Outfit, remote-control dices, etc.!\nUse dices to accumulate EXP and increase Chiori\'s Bond with you!\nChiori\'s Bond explained:\nBond Lv1: No effect\nBond Lv2: Earn 5% more coppers on the map\nBond Lv3: Earn 10% more coppers on the map\nBond Lv4: Earn 30% more coppers on the map\nBond LvMax: Earn 50% more coppers on the map\n\nMysterious chests are appearing on the map!\nItems that can be inside the mysterious chest: random number of copper, random sphere, Fortune Bag, Sage\'s Bag.\n\nAll the types of blocks:\nShopping mall: Get random number of copper when stopping on it.\nPresent shop: Get a random green gift when stopping on it.\nBoard game shop: Get a dice when stopping on it.\nJewelry shop: Get a random sphere when stopping on it.\nMahjong Soul bank: After using a dice or finish a lap on the map, copper will be deposited in the bank. \n- All the copper will be withdrew when stopping on Mahjong Soul bank. \nKaavi\'s fortune dial: Randomly select one of the following 6 effects.\n- Earn double coppers in the next move\n- Earn half coppers in the next move\n- Double the number of steps in the next move\n- Halve the number of steps in the next move\n- Move on 1 step\n- Refresh the location of mysterious chest","Walking in the shopping mall with Chiori. She\'s not having a good mood.","Walking in the shopping mall with Chiori. She\'s feeling normal.","Walking in the shopping mall with Chiori. She\'s feeling good.","Walking in the shopping mall with Chiori. She\'s feeling fantastic.","Chiori asked you to put away the small gifts that she couldn\'t carry anymore","Chiori seemed to be not interested in shiny things","Having fun in a board game shop with Chiori. Picked up a strange dice.","Arrived at Mahjong Soul Bank with Chiori. She withdrew some pocket money.","Opened a mysterious chest on the road. Wow, what\'s this...!","Chiori\'s Bond Lv1 is in effect!","Chiori\'s Bond Lv2 is in effect!","Chiori\'s Bond Lv3 is in effect!","Chiori\'s Bond Lv4 is in effect!","Chiori\'s Bond LvMax is in effect!","Passed the starting point for {0} time(s)! Earned a lap reward!","Successfully redeemed","Insufficient items.","Hot Spring Camp","Price:","Remaining","Donate","Level Up","Max Taiyakis from Battle daily:","After upgrading:","Taiyakis from Tea Party +","After upgrading +","Taiyakis from Battle Rank +","After upgrading +","You have reached max Wishing level","Wish to Ichihime","Wish to Kaguyahime","Wish to Wanjirou","Succesfully leveled up!","Insufficient Panda Ornaments","Max Wishing level reached","Do you want to remove this game log from Collection？","Season has ended","Path of Trial","No.{0}","","My Ranking:","Received Reward:","The reward has been sent to your Items - Decoration.","Oh! Careless Ichihime has lost the information about this Jyanshi.","","Exclusive Rewards","Dragon","Tiger","Preliminaries","Semi-Finals","Finals","Winner","Advance to the Finals","You have advanced to {0}","Calculating Stats...","Stage Available Attempts:","Cost:","The first attempt at each stage is free","{0}","Available Matches:","Expiry Date:","{0}/{1}/{2} {3}:{4}","Get {0} points to advance to {1}{2}","In Progress","","Failed to Advance","Get {0} points to obtain {1}{2}","Only one attempt for the Finals","You win","You\'ve completed the match","Epic Showdown Stage {0} Reward","Rewards","Epic Showdown Start!\nPreliminaries: 11/18 - 11/24 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\nSemi-Finals: 11/24 4:00 P.M. - 11/28 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\nFinals: 11/28 4:00 P.M. - 11/30 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\nPreliminaries/Semi-Finals/Finals attempt limits: 3/2/1\nThe first attempt at each stage is free, and each subsequent attempt costs 20,000 Coppers.\n\nYou can earn points after finishing matches in the Silver Room or other Ranked Room above after each attempt. (up to 4 matches for an attempt)\n4-Player Mahjong: 1/2/3/4 players will obtain 20/15/10/5 points respectively.\n3-Player Mahjong: 1/2/3 players will obtain 20/12/5 points respectively.\n\nAfter finishing each stage, the higher the points you have reached, the better the rewards.\nWhen the total points reach the next advancement milestone, you will be qualified for the next stage.\n\nIf you abandon the stage, you will still be able to claim earned rewards. (You cannot abandon the stage after finishing the 4 matches for an attempt)\nAbandoning will not affect advancement qualifications.","Abandon match? Abandoning will not affect Advancement qualifications, and players will still be able to claim earned rewards.","Current Stage:","Emote","Epic Showdown","Failed to Advance","Epic Showdown Rewards","Epic Showdown Point Rules","After finishing matches in the Silver Room or other Ranked Room above, you can earn points according to your ranking.","4-Player Mahjong","3-Player Mahjong","Points","Ranking","You can claim the rewards after finishing the matches of each stage.","Current points:","Counted Yakuman","Please mark your favourite character(s) first.","Do you want to spend {0} Coppers to enter? You can earn event points after finishing 4 matches in the Silver Room or other Ranked Room above after each attempt.","Entry Limit: Adept or above","{0}:","Please name this game log.","Restart","11/24 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/28 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/30 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","Exchanging","Please exchange your tiles in Hand anti-clockwise in this match","Please exchange your tiles in Hand with the oppsite player in this match","Please exchange your tiles in Hand clockwise in this match","Please choose 3 tiles in Hand to exchange","You have chosen {0} tiles","Waiting","Mail","Completed Achievements:","Achievement","Details","Rarity:","Progress","Complete all achievements in this category to claim rewards","12/25\n2:00 P.M.","12/29\n2:00 P.M.","1/2\n2:00 P.M.","Event Period: 12/21 - 1/6 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","-Current total winning point-","{0}pt","The winning points achieved during the event can improve the progress of making a snowman (exclude matches against AI)","The exchange rate of winning points: 4-player match: 1:1, 3-player match: 3:1.","Unlock the new snowmen during the event period to claim rewards!","Total:","Achievement:","Secret Achievement","??????","Completed","The latest version is now available, do you want to download it now?","Yes","No","Your current version is older than the required one, please go to download the latest version.","Download","Get Field Trip PT","Get Coppers","No Rank Limit\nNo Rank PT","Head to the Battle Room to play matches with special rules to obtain Taiyakis. There will be a daily limit of the Taiyaki obtainable from matches.","Besides, complete Tea Party missions to obtain Taiyakis as rewards.","Short on Taiyaki? You can head to the Wishing Shrine to donate to the three mysterious gods and boost your Taiyaki harvest.","Lastly, you may use Taiyakis to redeem your desired rewards at the Canteen!","Bloodshed Skirmish - Exchange tiles in hand","Bloodshed Skirmish - Special rules","Bloodshed Skirmish - Winning Settlement","Bloodshed Skirmish - Draw Settlement","In Battle of Asura with special rules, players need to select 3 tiles and give them to other Jyanshis randomly at the start. At the same time, they will receive 3 tiles from other Jyanshis.","There will be no Repeat Counter in Battle of Asura. The next match will start when the previous match ends with 3 winners or a Draw happens.","If there are yet to be 3 winners, the points obtained by the Jyanshi will be calculated immediately when winning, but their hands will remain hidden, and the match continues. Before the next match begins, the Jyanshi who has already won the match does not need to get involved, and the points remain unchanged.","When Draw happens, only the Jyanshi who has not won will face a No-Ten penalty. When a special Draw happens in the middle of the match, the match will be restarted.","Taiyaki can be obtained from Hot Spring Battle\n\nFinish the game in 1st place: +32\nFinish the game in 2nd place: 20\nFinish the game in 3rd place: +12\nFinish the game in 4th place: +6\nWin a game (Below Mangan): +2\nWin a game (Mangan): +4\nWin a game (Haneman): +6\nWin a game (Baiman): +8\nWin a game (Sanbaiman): +12\nWin a game (Yakuman or above): +16\n\n\nSpecial Rules: Battle of Asura Details\n\n- After the Hand distribution, select 3 tiles and exchange them with other players.\n- The ending condition of each match has been changed from 1 winner to 3 winners.\n- Upon winning, the points will be calculated in real-time, and the tiles in hand will remain hidden. The match will end when a player is busted. \n- Tsumo Loss will happen after the first player wins in a round (When the remaining players are less than 4, the points will be reduced when players call for Tsumo)\n- When a match ends, and there are less than 3 winners, it is regarded as a Draw. \n- There will be no Repeat Counter, regardless of whether the dealer has achieved Tenpai, the next match starts from 0 Repeat Counter. \n- When Draw happens during the match, regardless of whether there are winners, the match will restart from 0 Repeat Counter. \n- In the same match, players who have already won will not be participating in the Draw settlement.\n- When Draw happens, players who have not achieved Tenpai will pay 1000 points to each Tenpai player.\n- Players can choose to win when achieving Robbing a Kan (including Thirteen Orphans Concealed Quad). When a player wins by achieving Robbing a Kan, the Kan holds.\n- When Four-Kan Abortion happens after Robbing a Kan, Robbing a Kan holds, and the match will restart due to the Draw during the match.\n- Deal-in while in Riichi.\n- If the points left are above 1000 after paying for deal-in, the Riichi holds.\n- If the points left are below 1000 after paying for deal-in, the Riichi fails, and the match continues.\n- If the points left are below 0 after paying for deal-in, the match ends.\n- Player doesn\'t have to pay responsibility for causing other players\' Big Three Dragons or Four Big Winds.\n\nMatch mode: Battle of Asura - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points=100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nMatches played in this mode are not ranked\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st+260, 2nd+130, 3rd+95, 4th+60","Skip","Got it","Others","RECOM","Grade:","Now Playing","Not on the ranking","Server Ranking:","Top {0}%","Total Dispel Time(s):","Remaining HP:","Dispel Time(s)","Top {0}% - Top {1}%:","The rewards will be sent by mail when the event ends. Please don\'t forget to claim them.","Dispel {0} time(s)","Special Rules: Battle of Asura Details\n\n- After the Hand distribution, select 3 tiles and exchange them with other players.\n- The ending condition of each match has been changed from 1 winner to 3 winners.\n- Upon winning, the points will be calculated in real-time, and the tiles in hand will remain hidden. The match will end when a player is busted. \n- Tsumo Loss will happen after the first player wins in a round (When the remaining players are less than 4, the points will be reduced when players call for Tsumo)\n- When a match ends, and there are less than 3 winners, it is regarded as a Draw. \n- There will be no Repeat Counter, regardless of whether the dealer has achieved Tenpai, the next match starts from 0 Repeat Counter. \n- When Draw happens during the match, regardless of whether there are winners, the match will restart from 0 Repeat Counter. \n- In the same match, players who have already won will not be participating in the Draw settlement.\n- When Draw happens, players who have not achieved Tenpai will pay 1000 points to each Tenpai player.\n- Players can choose to win when achieving Robbing a Kan (including Thirteen Orphans Concealed Quad). When a player wins by achieving Robbing a Kan, the Kan holds.\n- When Four-Kan Abortion happens after Robbing a Kan, Robbing a Kan holds, and the match will restart due to the Draw during the match.\n- Deal-in while in Riichi.\n- If the points left are above 1000 after paying for deal-in, the Riichi holds.\n- If the points left are below 1000 after paying for deal-in, the Riichi fails, and the match continues.\n- If the points left are below 0 after paying for deal-in, the match ends.\n- Player doesn\'t have to pay responsibility for causing other players\' Big Three Dragons or Four Big Winds.\n\nMatch mode: Battle of Asura - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points=100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nMatches played in this mode are not ranked\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st+260, 2nd+130, 3rd+95, 4th+60\nBond Point Bonus: 40\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","Lobby","Matches","During the event, points earned in Ranked Match and Battle of Asura room can be used to dispel the Monster Nian.","The exchange rate of winning points: 4-player Ranked Match: 1:1, Other Modes: 3:1.","When the event ends, you can obtain extra rewards according to your server ranking of dispel times.","Nian Incoming - Spring Festival Event\nEvent Period: 2/5 - 2/21 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nIn the midst of Spring Festival celebration, the Monster Nian approaches!\nIt\'s said that joyful mahjong games can protect you from evil!\nJoin the matches to dispel Nian together!\n\nThe exchange rate of winning points which earned in Ranked Match and Battle of Asura room:\n4-player Ranked Match: 1:1\n3-player Ranked Match: 3:1\nBattle of Asura: 3:1\n\nThe event point limit will increase progressively during the event.\nAfter 2/9 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7), the event point limit will be removed, and the dispel time leaderboard will be unlocked.\nWhen the event ends, you can obtain extra rewards according to your server ranking of dispel times. For more information, please check [Ranking Rewards] in Leaderboard.","Battle of Asura","2/6\n2:00 P.M.","2/7\n2:00 P.M.","2/8\n2:00 P.M.","Leaderboard will be unlocked after 2/9 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7).","Calculating","Special Rules: Battle of Asura Details\n\n- After the Hand distribution, select 3 tiles and exchange them with other players.\n- The ending condition of each match has been changed from 1 winner to 3 winners.\n- Upon winning, the points will be calculated in real-time, and the tiles in hand will remain hidden. The match will end when a player is busted. \n- Tsumo Loss will happen after the first player wins in a round (When the remaining players are less than 4, the points will be reduced when players call for Tsumo)\n- When a match ends, and there are less than 3 winners, it is regarded as a Draw. \n- There will be no Repeat Counter, regardless of whether the dealer has achieved Tenpai, the next match starts from 0 Repeat Counter. \n- When Draw happens during the match, regardless of whether there are winners, the match will restart from 0 Repeat Counter. \n- In the same match, players who have already won will not be participating in the Draw settlement.\n- When Draw happens, players who have not achieved Tenpai will pay 1000 points to each Tenpai player.\n- Players can choose to win when achieving Robbing a Kan (including Thirteen Orphans Concealed Quad). When a player wins by achieving Robbing a Kan, the Kan holds.\n- When Four-Kan Abortion happens after Robbing a Kan, Robbing a Kan holds, and the match will restart due to the Draw during the match.\n- Deal-in while in Riichi.\n- If the points left are above 1000 after paying for deal-in, the Riichi holds.\n- If the points left are below 1000 after paying for deal-in, the Riichi fails, and the match continues.\n- If the points left are below 0 after paying for deal-in, the match ends.\n- Player doesn\'t have to pay responsibility for causing other players\' Big Three Dragons or Four Big Winds.","Please select three tiles of the same suit to exchange.","Round{0}","Event","Bloodshed Skirmish","The Field Trip PT that can be achieved from the Bloodshed Skirmish Event Room:\n\nAchieve 1st place: +20,000\nAchieve 2nd place: +12,000\nAchieve 3rd place: +6,000\nAchieve 4th place: +2,000\n\nWinning (1 Han): +1,000\nWinning (2 Han): +2,000\nWinning (3 Han): +3,000\nWinning (4 Han): +4,000\nWinning (5 Han): +6,000\nWinning (6 Han and above): +8,000\n\nSpecial Rules: Bloodshed Skirmish Instructions\n\n—A total of 108 tiles without Honor tiles will be used.\n—After the distribution of tiles, pick 3 tiles of the same suit and exchange them with other Jyanshis.\n—Players need to pick an unwanted suit each round, and they can only win when they don\'t have tiles of that suit in hand.\n\n—There is no Riichi, Chii, Furiten, Wanpai (Dora Indicator, Kan Dora Indicator and Rinshan Tile) and Dora.\n—Ending a round requires 3 Tenpai players instead of 1.\n—There is no consecutive dealer, and the game ends after 4 rounds. The first winning Jyanshi in each round will be the next dealer.\n—When someone wins, the points will be calculated immediately and the /hand will not be shown. The round ends when a Jyanshi gets busted.\n—When a round ends, the round is regarded as Draw if there are fewer than 3 winning players.\n\n—When Concealed Quad is achieved, take 2000 points from every active Jyanshi.\n—When Open Quad is achieved, take 2000 points from the Jyanshi who makes this Quad.\n—Take 1000 points from each Jyanshi when adding to an Open Triplet with a drawn tile.\n—No points will be taken from other Jyanshi(s) when using a tile in your own hand to complete a Quad.\n—When Robbing a Kan occurs when you are calling a Kan, the Kan will not be completed, and no point will be taken from other Jyanshi(s).\n—Upon Draw, if some Jyanshis didn\'t achieve Tenpai, the points taken through completing Kans during that round will be returned.\n\n—Within the same round, the winning Jyanshi(s) will not be involved in the following Draw calculation:\n—Upon Draw, the Jyanshi(s) who is not yet Tenpai should give points to the Jyanshi(s) who is. The points will be calculated according to the highest possible Han of their Tenpai.\n—Upon Draw, if there is still at least one tile from the unwanted suit in one\'s Hand, one needs to pay at least 8000 points (4 Han) to each Jyanshi (regardless of Tenpai or not). If one\'s Tenpai is worth 16000 points (5 Han) or above, the Jyanshi instead will have to pay whatever the Tenpai\'s worth should be.\n\n—The correlation between Han numbers and points when winning:\n1 Han = 1000 Points\n2 Han = 2000 Points\n3 Han = 4000 Points\n4 Han = 8000 Points\n5 Han = 16000 Points\n6 Han (Max) = 32000 Points\n—When achieve Ron, take corresponding points from players who deal you in.\n—Upon achieving Tsumo, take corresponding points from all players with an additional 1000 points.\n\nRank Limit: N/A\nOrder Bonus: 1st+15, 2nd+5, 3rd-5, 4th-15\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points=100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nNo Rank Bonus\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st+260, 2nd+130, 3rd+95, 4th+60\nBond Point Bonus: 40\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","4 Han","5 Han","Please choose one suit that you don\'t need.","Get Field Trip PT by playing matches in the Field Trip Inn. The daily-obtainable Field Trip PT has an upper limit.","Complete missions on the Notice Board to obtain Field Trip PT and Panda Ornaments.","Field Trip PT can be obtained more easily by using Panda Ornaments in the Training.","By accumulating Field Trip PT, more event storylines will be unlocked in Scenic Pavilion. Rewards can be redeemed at the Tower of the Wise.","As stated in the special rules of the Bloodshed Skirmish, there will be a total of 108 Tiles without Honor tiles. Player needs to select 3 tiles of the same suit and randomly give them to other Jyanshis, and at the same time receive 3 tiles from them. There will be no consecutive dealer, and there will be a total of 4 rounds.","Players need to pick an unwanted suit each round, and they can only win when they don\'t have tiles of that suit in Hand. The first player who wins in each round will be the dealer in the next round. There will be no Furiten. The next round commences when there are 3 winners or when Draw is triggered.","If there are less than three winning players, points will be calculated immediately.However, the winner\'s hand will not be shown, and the round will continue.Before the next round begins, the winning Jyanshi(s) does not need to draw,and there will be no changes in their points.","A player can obtain additional points from other players upon achieving Open Quad and Concealed Quad or by completing a Quad with a newly-drawn tile. However, if the player is not Tenpai upon Draw, the obtained points will be returned.","Upon Draw, the Jyanshi(s) who is not yet Tenpai need to give points to the Jyanshi(s) who is. The points will be calculated according to the highest possible Han of their Tenpai. If there is still at least one tile from the unwanted suit in their hand, the points given will be calculated as 4 Han or above.","Unlock at {0}PT","The new missions will be unlocked at {0}.","4/22 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/23 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/24 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/25 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/26 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/27 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/28 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/29 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/30 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","5/1 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","The Field Trip PT that can be achieved from the DoraDorara Event Room:\n\nAchieve 1st place: +20,000\nAchieve 2nd place: +12,000\nAchieve 3rd place: +6,000\nAchieve 4th place: +2,000\n\nWinning (below Mangan): +3,000\nWinning (Mangan): +6,000\nWinning (Haneman): +9,000\nWinning (Baiman): +12,000\nWinning (Sanbaiman): +18,000\nWinning (Yakuman and above): +24,000\n\nSpecial Rules: DoraDorara Mode Details\n4-player East limited. Each game starts with 3 Dora indicators already revealed and a maximum amount of Dora indicators at 5. The first 2 Kans called in a game will reveal 1 Dora indicator each, but any Kan called beyond the first 2 will no longer reveal any Dora indicator.\n\nRank Limit: N/A\n\nOrder Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +5, 3rd -5, 4th -15\n\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\n\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\n\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\n\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\n\nIchihime’s Gift Box Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","Locked","","","","","","","","","","","","","","Please claim the event rewards at the Department Store before 11/17 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7).","Comment","Like","Unlike","@","Oops! It looks like you have reached the end, nyaa~","Announcement","Currently there are no announcement","Loading","","Use 1 ticket to take part in Epic Showdown?","*In Celestial Rank, the Initial Point is 10 Soul Points,\n and upgrades when 20 Soul Points is reached.","*East Round Match Order Bonus:\n 1st +0.3, 2nd +0.1, 3rd -0.1, 4th -0.3","*Hanchan Match Order Bonus:\n 1st +0.5, 2nd +0.2, 3rd -0.2, 4th -0.5","* If all players in a match are at Celestial Rank,\n then the Soul Point change will be doubled.","*In Celestial Rank, the Initial Point is 10 Soul Points,\n and upgrades when 20\nSoul Points is reached.","*East Round Match Order Bonus:\n 1st +0.3, 2nd +0, 3rd -0.3","*Hanchan Match Order Bonus:\n 1st +0.5, 2nd +0, 3rd -0.5","12 Victories Rewards","Highest\nvictory number","Accumulated\nvictory number","Tickets owned:","Event ends at 12/19 6:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","Current rewards:","Event ends at 12/19 6:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","","match(es) till gift box is upgraded","Victories in this round:","Failures allowed:","Rewards can be claimed after finishing all matches in this round.","Victories","Attribute Points","Introduction","Current","Battle Log","Cat Warrior Ichihime","Current Stage","Pay Coppers x75,000 to enter Epic Showdown?","Are you sure to surrender? After surrender you will get the rewards based on your wins.","Epic Showdown Event\n\nEvent Time: 12/12 7:00 P.M. - 12/19 6:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\n- Use 1 Epic Showdown Ticket or 75,000 Coppers to enter the challenge.\n- After each match, the match is counted as a win if you are at 1st or 2nd place and a failure if you are at 3rd or 4th place\n- A round of challenge ends after three failures and rewards will be given out based on the number of wins.\n- Challenge is completed successfully with 12 wins, and 12 Win Rewards will be given out.\n- You can abandon the challenge, and rewards will be given out based on the number of wins immediately.\n- You can enter the challenge up to 5 times a day, the daily limit will be refreshed at 2:00 P.M. every day.\n- After 12/19 1:59 P.M., you can only enter the challenge via ticket. Entry with Coppers will not be possible.\n\nEpic Showdown Calculation Details\nMatch Mode: Event Match - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nOrder Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +5, 3rd -5, 4th -15\nCoppers and Rank Bonus will not be calculated.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","You have reached the challenge limit today, please come back tomorrow.","Insufficient Coppers","Exit","Animated Outfit","Animation","View Animation","Default","Touch","Celebration","After Acquirement","Acquirement Animation loading failed","Special Rules: Battle of Clairvoyance Instructions\n\n- This mode uses a special set of Mahjong tiles. In each kind of tile, three out of four will be transparent.\n- No Red Five.\n- No Multiple Ron.\n- When Auto Arrange is On, normal tiles and transparent tiles will be arranged in the usual order.\n- Player\'s tiles arrangement won\'t be applied in other players\' views.\n- You will see other players\' tiles with all transparent ones on one side and with their projections on the table.\n- When you call for a Chii or Pon, you can decide whether to use normal or transparent tiles.\n\nMatch Mode: Battle of Clairvoyance - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nNo rank Bonus\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","This mode uses a special set of Mahjong tiles. In each kind of tile, three out of four will be transparent, nyaa. There will be no Red Five (i.e. no Red 5 Man, Red 5 Pin, or Red 5 Sou) in this mode, nyaa!","When multiple players call for a Ron on a discarded tile, the one counterclockwise closest to the player who dealt in wins, no multiple Ron, nyaa!","Player\'s tile arrangement won\'t be applied in other players\' views, nyaa. You will see other players\' tiles with all transparent ones on one side and with their projections on the table, nyaa.","When you call for a Chii or Pon, you can decide whether to use normal or transparent tiles, nyaa!","Special Rules: Battle of Darkness Instructions\n\n- When you discard a tile, you can choose to pay 1000 points to discard it [concealed].\n-- Other players cannot call for a Chii, Pon, Kan or Ron on the concealed tile, nor will it trigger Furiten for any player including the one who discarded it.\n-- When a player has less than 1000 points, discarding a tile concealed will not be possible.\n-- When a player has less than 2000 points, declaring Riichi concealed will not be possible.\n\n- When other players discard a tile concealed, you can pay 2000 points to [reveal] it.\n-- Aside from the player who discarded the tile concealed, all the other players will decide whether to reveal it at the same time.\n-- If multiple players decide to reveal the concealed tile, the one counterclockwise closest to the player discarding the tile will pay the points.\n-- After the reveal, it\'s no longer a concealed tile, it becomes open for everyone to see, and can be called for a Chii, Pon, Kan or Ron.\n-- When a player has less than 2000 points, revealing a concealed tile will not be possible.\n\n- When a concealed tile is about to be revealed, the player discarding the tile can pay 4000 points to keep it [locked] in concealed mode.\n-- A locked tile will stay concealed, and other players cannot call for a Chii, Pon, Kan or Ron on it.\n-- When a player has less than 4000 points, locking a concealed tile will not be possible.\n\n- Bet points paid for concealing, revealing and locking tiles will be put on the table and collected by the next player to win a hand.\n- When multiple players call for a Ron on a discarded tile, the one counterclockwise closest to the player discarding the tile will collect all bets on the table (including Riichi and round bet).\n- When the match ends, any unclaimed bet will be given to the 1st place player.\n- Concealed tiles will not interfere with Mangan at Draw, that is, only non-concealed tiles will be counted towards Mangan at Draw.\n\nMatch Mode: Battle of Darkness - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","When you discard a tile, you can choose to pay 1000 points to discard it [concealed], nyaa! Other players cannot call for a Chii, Pon, Kan or Ron on the concealed tile, nor will it trigger Furiten for any player including yourself, nyaa! Please note declaring Riichi with a concealed tile will cost you 2000 points, nyaa.","When other players discard a tile concealed, you can pay 2000 points to [reveal] it, nyaa. If multiple players decide to reveal the concealed tile, the one counterclockwise closest to the player discarding the tile will pay the points, nyaa. After the reveal, it\'s no longer a concealed tile, becomes open for everyone to see, and can be called for a Chii, Pon, Kan or Ron, nyaa!","When a concealed tile is about to be revealed, the player discarding the tile can pay 4000 points to keep it [locked] in concealed mode, nyaa. A locked tile will stay concealed, and other players cannot ever call for a Chii, Pon, Kan or Ron on it, nyaa! Players can only see what the locked tile is in Log after the match, nyaa.","Bet points paid for concealing, revealing and locking tiles will be put on the table and collected by the next player to win a hand, nyaa! When multiple players call for a Ron on a discarded tile, the one counterclockwise closest to the player discarding the tile will collect all bets on the table, nyaa. When the match ends, any unclaimed bet will be given to the 1st place player, nyaa!","The Night of Legends Event starts, nyaa! During the event, two special game modes Battle of Clairvoyance and Battle of Darkness are open for a limited time, nyaa!","Special game mode Battle of Darkness is a psychological battle on the Mahjong table full of suspense, nyaa! By paying certain amounts of bet points, you can conceal (discarding a tile face down), reveal (flipping other player\'s concealed tile), or lock (block a reveal and keep a concealed tile face down), nyaa. An intense and exciting time-limited special rule, check it out, nyaa!","Special game mode Battle of Clairvoyance needs you to take advantage of the information available, nyaa! In each kind of tile, three out of four will be transparent and can be seen by everyone, nyaa. A legendary special rule shrouded in myths, try it out, nyaa!","Complete missions during the event and collect rewards in Department Store, nyaa. You can view the event story in Cinema, nyaa!","Will be unlocked on 11/5 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","New missions will be unlocked on {0}","10/28 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","10/29 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","10/30 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","10/31 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","11/1 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","11/2 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","11/3 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","11/4 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","11/5 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","Battle of Clairvoyance","Battle of Darkness","About Conceal","About Reveal","About Lock","About Bet Points","About the Tiles","No Multiple Ron","About Tile Arrangement","Choose Tiles for the Call","Special Rules: Battle of Clairvoyance Instructions\n\n- This mode uses a special set of Mahjong tiles. In each kind of tile, three out of four will be transparent.\n- No Red Five.\n- No Multiple Ron.\n- When Auto Arrange is On, normal tiles and transparent tiles will be arranged in the usual order.\n- Player\'s tiles arrangement won\'t be applied in other players\' views.\n- You will see other players\' tiles with all transparent ones on one side and with their projections on the table.\n- When you call for a Chii or Pon, you can decide whether to use normal or transparent tiles.","Special Rules: Battle of Darkness Instructions\n\n- When you discard a tile, you can choose to pay 1000 points to discard it [concealed].\n-- Other players cannot call for a Chii, Pon, Kan or Ron on the concealed tile, nor will it trigger Furiten for any player including the one who discarded it.\n-- When a player has less than 1000 points, discarding a tile concealed will not be possible.\n-- When a player has less than 2000 points, declaring Riichi concealed will not be possible.\n\n- When other players discard a tile concealed, you can pay 2000 points to [reveal] it.\n-- Aside from the player who discarded the tile concealed, all the other players will decide whether to reveal it at the same time.\n-- If multiple players decide to reveal the concealed tile, the one counterclockwise closest to the player discarding the tile will pay the points.\n-- After the reveal, it\'s no longer a concealed tile, it becomes open for everyone to see, and can be called for a Chii, Pon, Kan or Ron.\n-- When a player has less than 2000 points, revealing a concealed tile will not be possible.\n\n- When a concealed tile is about to be revealed, the player discarding the tile can pay 4000 points to keep it [locked] in concealed mode.\n-- A locked tile will stay concealed, and other players cannot call for a Chii, Pon, Kan or Ron on it.\n-- When a player has less than 4000 points, locking a concealed tile will not be possible.\n\n- Bet points paid for concealing, revealing and locking tiles will be put on the table and collected by the next player to win a hand.\n- When multiple players call for a Ron on a discarded tile, the one counterclockwise closest to the player discarding the tile will collect all bets on the table (including Riichi and round bet).\n- When the match ends, any unclaimed bet will be given to the 1st place player.\n- Concealed tiles will not interfere with Mangan at Draw, that is, only non-concealed tiles will be counted towards Mangan at Draw.","Match watching interrupted, retry now?","","The event will end soon. Thereafter, entry with Coppers will not be possible.","Reward unlocks at Bond {0}","Claim Bond {0} Reward","Lv1","Lv2","Lv3","Lv4","Lv5","In this beautiful snowy winter, let\'s go on a journey to pursue the way of a Nishiba-ryu swordsman!\n\nEvent Period: 12/21 - 1/7 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nComplete daily event missions to get dices (except matches played against AI).\nComplete specified number of laps on the event map to collect event rewards.\n\nUse dices to accumulate experience to upgrade Kazuha\'s level!\nKazuha\'s levels:\nLv1: No effect\nLv2: Get +5% more Copper on the map\nLv3: Get +10% more Copper on the map\nLv4: Get +30% more Copper on the map\nLvMax: Get +50% more Copper on the map\n\nMysterious chests are appearing on the map!\nItems that could be inside a mysterious chest: random number of Copper, random sphere, Fortune Bag, Sage\'s Bag.\n\nTypes of block:\nMeditation Practice: Get random number of Copper when stopping on it.\nPhysical Training: Get a random green gift when stopping on it.\nBoard Game Shop: Get a dice when stopping on it.\nKendo Training: Get a random sphere when stopping on it.\nMahjong Soul Bank: After using a dice or finishing a lap on the map, Copper will be deposited in the bank.\n- All the Copper will be withdrawn when stopping on Mahjong Soul Bank.\nKaavi\'s Fortune Dial: Randomly select one of the following 6 effects.\n- Earn double Coppers in the next move\n- Earn half Coppers in the next move\n- Double the number of steps in the next move\n- Halve the number of steps in the next move\n- Move on 1 step\n- Refresh the location of mysterious chest","Meditation Practice not going well...","Meditation Practice going not bad.","Meditation Practice going well.","Meditation Practice going greatly.","Found small gift during physical training.","Found something sparkling in Kendo training.","Picked up a strange dice in board game shop.","Arrived at Mahjong Soul Bank and withdrew all the Coppers!","Opened a mysterious chest on the road. Wow, what\'s this...!","Kazuha\'s Lv1 bonus effect activated!","Kazuha\'s Lv2 bonus effect activated!","Kazuha\'s Lv3 bonus effect activated!","Kazuha\'s Lv4 bonus effect activated!","Kazuha\'s LvMax bonus effect activated!","Entry requires Adept I or above in either 4-Player or 3-Player.","Your rank does not meet the entry requirement.","Greeting","Gifts given away today:","Gifts received today:","Give away {0} x1","Confirm Give Away","Give Away","(Owned: {0})","Feed {0} time(s)","Claimed: {0}/30","Insufficient ingredients","Gifts given away today reached max limit.","Claimable today: {0}/10","During event, complete daily missions to get ingredients.\nAsk friends for aid. You can give each other ingredients.\nCollect 5 types of ingredients, feed them to Monster Nian to get rewards.","Progress","","A Feast for Nian - Spring Festival Event\nEvent Period: 1/25 - 2/15 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nIn the midst of Spring Festival celebrations, another Monster Nian arrives!\nThis year, Nian is docile and no longer making trouble.\nCollect food ingredients, feed them to Nian and get rewards!\n\nDuring the event, complete daily missions to get random ingredients.\nYou can earn winning points in Ranked Match, Tournament Match and Friendly Match with no AI. The conversion rate of winning points earned is as followed:\n4-Player Ranked/Friendly Match: 1:1\n3-Player Ranked/Friendly Match: 3:1\nTournament Match - Battle of Asura: 3:1\nTournament Match - Bloodshed Skirmish: 3:1\nTournament Match - DoraDorara: 3:1\nDaily max limit of accumulated winning points is 30,000 and resets every day at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nYou can give your friends ingredients (Max limit 5 a day, resets every day at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7))\nIngredients received from friends can be claimed from Mail (Max limit 5 a day, resets every day at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7))\n\nWhen you have collected all 5 types of ingredients, feed them to the Nian to get rewards!\nRewards for each feeding can be checked out in Reward Details.\nFor the first 30 feedings, special rewards are given; starting from the 31st feeding, 500 Coppers will be rewarded each time.","Daily Mission","Reward List","Feed 31 times and more","Tap food ingredient to give it away to friend.","Resets every day at\n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Exit screen adjustment now? Unsaved changes will be lost.","Collection: {0}/15","Incomplete","Collect all cards to claim the reward.","-","Sakura Path","Bamboo Path","This game mode combines rules of card game and Mahjong, making every match different!","When a match starts, one card will be drawn from each category (Dealer Cards, Chance Cards and Destiny Cards) and they will become the additional rules of this match.","Dreamland Odyssey","Special Rules: Dreamland Odyssey Instructions\n\n- Before a match starts, one card will be drawn from each category (Dealer Cards, Chance Cards and Destiny Cards). The three cards drawn will become the additional rules of this match.\n- You can check out the rules of each card during the match.\n- The cards you have played in Dreamland Odyssey will be unlocked for review in Display Cabinet.\n\nAbout Event Pts\n\nDuring the event, play Ranked Match or Dreamland Odyssey and you will get Event Pts as follows:\n4-Player: \n1st Place +200\n2nd Place +120\n3rd Place +60\n4th Place +20\n3-Player:\n1st Place +120\n2nd Place +60\n3rd Place +20\n\nWinning (Score below Mangan) +30\nWinning (Mangan) +60\nWinning (Haneman) +90\nWinning (Baiman) +120\nWinning (Sanbaiman) +180\nWinning (Yakuman and above) +240\n\nGame Mode: Dreamland Odyssey - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","Special Rules: Dreamland Odyssey Instructions\n\n- Before a match starts, one card will be drawn from each category (Dealer Cards, Chance Cards and Destiny Cards). The three cards drawn will become the additional rules of this match.\n- You can check out the rules of each card during the match.","The War of Love event has started, nyaa! Go to Event page - Tabletop Game to experience the new game mode Dreamland Odyssey, nyaa! You can earn Event Pts by playing Event Match or Ranked Match, read Rules for more information.","During the event, you can also complete missions on School Project to get Event Pts.","When you have accumulated enough Event Pts, you can claim various rewards on Activity Log.","In Display Cabinet, you can review all cards you have encountered in the event game mode. You can also review the event stories here.","Will be unlocked on 5/1 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","Will be unlocked on 5/6 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","The new missions will be unlocked at {0}.","4/27 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","4/28 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","4/29 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","4/30 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","5/1 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","5/2 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","5/3 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","5/4 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","5/5 2:00 P.M.(UTC-7)","Character","Voice","Change voice settings for individual characters","Dorm Display","Change display status for individual characters in Dorm","Click to expand","You cannot hide the character currently in use","Special Rules","4 Matches","8 Matches","한국어","???","1st","2nd","3rd","Get Voting Ticket","Votes Cast","Vote","Votes: {0}","Ranking","Vote","Ranking updated:","Incomplete","Claimed","Owned:","Ticket(s)","Use Voting Ticket x1 on {0}","Insufficient Voting Ticket","Voted!","Contact Us","TERMS OF SERVICE","PRIVACY POLICY","The event is over","TileSet","Can only be set at homepage","Help","EMPTY","Go Vote","Use Voting Ticket x10 on {0}","Special Rules: Bloodshed Skirmish Instructions\n\n—A total of 108 tiles without Honor tiles will be used.\n—After the distribution of tiles, pick 3 tiles of the same suit and exchange them with other Jyanshis.\n—Players need to pick an unwanted suit each round, and they can only win when they don\'t have tiles of that suit in hand.\n\n—There is no Riichi, Chii, Furiten, Wanpai (Dora Indicator, Kan Dora Indicator and Rinshan Tile) and Dora.\n—Ending a round requires 3 Tenpai players instead of 1.\n—There is no consecutive dealer, and the game ends after 4 rounds. The first winning Jyanshi in each round will be the next dealer.\n—When someone wins, the points will be calculated immediately and the /hand will not be shown. The round ends when a Jyanshi gets busted.\n—When a round ends, the round is regarded as Draw if there are fewer than 3 winning players.\n\n—When Concealed Quad is achieved, take 2000 points from every active Jyanshi.\n—When Open Quad is achieved, take 2000 points from the Jyanshi who makes this Quad.\n—Take 1000 points from each Jyanshi when adding to an Open Triplet with a drawn tile.\n—No points will be taken from other Jyanshi(s) when using a tile in your own hand to complete a Quad.\n—When Robbing a Kan occurs when you are calling a Kan, the Kan will not be completed, and no point will be taken from other Jyanshi(s).\n—Upon Draw, if some Jyanshis didn\'t achieve Tenpai, the points taken through completing Kans during that round will be returned.\n\n—Within the same round, the winning Jyanshi(s) will not be involved in the following Draw calculation:\n—Upon Draw, the Jyanshi(s) who is not yet Tenpai should give points to the Jyanshi(s) who is. The points will be calculated according to the highest possible Han of their Tenpai.\n—Upon Draw, if there is still at least one tile from the unwanted suit in one\'s Hand, one needs to pay at least 8000 points (4 Han) to each Jyanshi (regardless of Tenpai or not). If one\'s Tenpai is worth 16000 points (5 Han) or above, the Jyanshi instead will have to pay whatever the Tenpai\'s worth should be.\n\n—The correlation between Han numbers and points when winning:\n1 Han = 1000 Points\n2 Han = 2000 Points\n3 Han = 4000 Points\n4 Han = 8000 Points\n5 Han = 16000 Points\n6 Han (Max) = 32000 Points\n—When achieve Ron, take corresponding points from players who deal you in.\n—Upon achieving Tsumo, take corresponding points from all players with an additional 1000 points.","Special Rules: DoraDorara Mode Details\nEach game starts with 3 Dora indicators already revealed and a maximum amount of Dora indicators at 5. The first 2 Kans called in a game will reveal 1 Dora indicator each, but any Kan called beyond the first 2 will no longer reveal any Dora indicator.","Starting Points: 50,000\nLength: 4 Round\nWaiting Time: 5+20","Special Rules: Bloodshed Skirmish Instructions\n\n—A total of 108 tiles without Honor tiles will be used.\n—After the distribution of tiles, pick 3 tiles of the same suit and exchange them with other Jyanshis.\n—Players need to pick an unwanted suit each round, and they can only win when they don\'t have tiles of that suit in hand.\n\n—There is no Riichi, Chii, Furiten, Wanpai (Dora Indicator, Kan Dora Indicator and Rinshan Tile) and Dora.\n—Ending a round requires 3 Tenpai players instead of 1.\n—There is no consecutive dealer, and the game ends after 4 rounds. The first winning Jyanshi in each round will be the next dealer.\n—When someone wins, the points will be calculated immediately and the /hand will not be shown. The round ends when a Jyanshi gets busted.\n—When a round ends, the round is regarded as Draw if there are fewer than 3 winning players.\n\n—When Concealed Quad is achieved, take 2000 points from every active Jyanshi.\n—When Open Quad is achieved, take 2000 points from the Jyanshi who makes this Quad.\n—Take 1000 points from each Jyanshi when adding to an Open Triplet with a drawn tile.\n—No points will be taken from other Jyanshi(s) when using a tile in your own hand to complete a Quad.\n—When Robbing a Kan occurs when you are calling a Kan, the Kan will not be completed, and no point will be taken from other Jyanshi(s).\n—Upon Draw, if some Jyanshis didn\'t achieve Tenpai, the points taken through completing Kans during that round will be returned.\n\n—Within the same round, the winning Jyanshi(s) will not be involved in the following Draw calculation:\n—Upon Draw, the Jyanshi(s) who is not yet Tenpai should give points to the Jyanshi(s) who is. The points will be calculated according to the highest possible Han of their Tenpai.\n—Upon Draw, if there is still at least one tile from the unwanted suit in one\'s Hand, one needs to pay at least 8000 points (4 Han) to each Jyanshi (regardless of Tenpai or not). If one\'s Tenpai is worth 16000 points (5 Han) or above, the Jyanshi instead will have to pay whatever the Tenpai\'s worth should be.\n\n—The correlation between Han numbers and points when winning:\n1 Han = 1000 Points\n2 Han = 2000 Points\n3 Han = 4000 Points\n4 Han = 8000 Points\n5 Han = 16000 Points\n6 Han (Max) = 32000 Points\n—When achieve Ron, take corresponding points from players who deal you in.\n—Upon achieving Tsumo, take corresponding points from all players with an additional 1000 points.\n\nRank Limit: N/A\nOrder Bonus: 1st+15, 2nd+5, 3rd-5, 4th-15\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points=100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nNo Rank Bonus\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st+260, 2nd+130, 3rd+95, 4th+60\nBond Point Bonus: 40\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","Special Rules: DoraDorara Instructions\n4-player East limited mode. Each game starts with 3 Dora indicators already revealed and a maximum amount of Dora indicators at 5. The first 2 Kans called in a game will reveal 1 Dora indicator each, but any Kan called beyond the first 2 will no longer reveal any Dora indicator.\n\nGame Mode: DoraDorara - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nOrder Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +5, 3rd -5, 4th -15\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60\nBond Point Bonus: 40\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","DoraDorara","Please choose an outfit. You can see an outfit\'s details by tapping on it twice.","Are you sure you want to use Outfit Ticket x1 to receive {0}?","Outfit Ticket","You have successfully received {0}.","Skill has reached max level.","Use","x1 to unlock","Insufficient unlock item.","Are you sure you want to use Éternité Coupon x1 to unlock another story path?","Another story path has been unlocked.","Are you sure you want to use Skill Pt x{0} to level up {1}?","Successfully leveled up!","All","Exit","Change name to","Please unlock the previous story first.","Empty","Empty","Empty","No search result, please check Friend\'s ID","Empty","Loading...","Empty","Empty","Empty","Empty","Empty","Empty","1 Rename Scroll is needed to change your nickname, go buy it in Shop - Fortune?","You haven\'t gotten this character yet.","Please input the game log link","You can use this Outfit if you own this character.","Right Click for Auto Draw & Discard","Please input Friend ID","Click to edit your introduction.","This button/gesture doesn\'t work on this page","Are you sure you want to quit the game?","Room","Duel of Divination","In this vast universe, can you find the star that\'s shining only for you?","Every turn, when a player is to draw a tile, they can choose from one of three tiles presented.","Sense the future, make your choice and play this super exciting 4-Player East game!","Special Rules: Duel of Divination Instructions\n\n- At the start of each round, when the dealer is about to draw a tile, 3 tiles will be revealed from the tile wall and the revealed tiles will become the Option Tiles.\n- Every time a player is to draw a tile normally or after a Kan, they can choose from one of the three Option Tiles.\n- The Option Tiles not chosen by the player will be kept.\n\n- Option Tiles are visible to all players.\n- Before a player is about to draw a tile, new tiles will be revealed from the tile wall to make sure that there are 3 Option Tiles available.\n- If 3 tiles or fewer are left in the tile wall, no more Option Tiles will be revealed, and players cannot call for Kan anymore.\n\n*If the requirements for Blessing of Earth are fulfilled and the player wins by choosing a tile from the Option Tiles, Blessing of Earth is achieved.\n*If the requirements for Ippatsu are fulfilled and the player wins by choosing a tile from the Option Tiles, Ippatsu is achieved.\n*If the player wins by choosing a tile after a Kan from the Option Tiles, After a Kan is achieved.\n* In the Duel of Divination mode, the Auto Draw&Discard function is disabled.\n\nAbout Wishing Pts\nDuring the event, play Ranked Match or Duel of Divination and you will get Wishing Pts as follows:\n4-Player: \n1st Place +200\n2nd Place +120\n3rd Place +60\n4th Place +20\n3-Player:\n1st Place +120\n2nd Place +60\n3rd Place +20\n\nWinning (Score below Mangan) +30\nWinning (Mangan) +60\nWinning (Haneman) +90\nWinning (Baiman) +120\nWinning (Sanbaiman) +180\nWinning (Yakuman and above) +240\n\nGame Mode: Duel of Divination - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","Special Rules: Duel of Divination Instructions\n\n- At the start of each round, when the dealer is about to draw a tile, 3 tiles will be revealed from the tile wall and the revealed tiles will become the Option Tiles.\n- Every time a player is to draw a tile normally or after a Kan, they can choose from one of the three Option Tiles.\n- The Option Tiles not chosen by the player will be kept.\n\n- Option Tiles are visible to all players.\n- Before a player is about to draw a tile, new tiles will be revealed from the tile wall to make sure that there are 3 Option Tiles available.\n- If 3 tiles or fewer are left in the tile wall, no more Option Tiles will be revealed, and players cannot call for Kan anymore.\n\n*If the requirements for Blessing of Earth are fulfilled and the player wins by choosing a tile from the Option Tiles, Blessing of Earth is achieved.\n*If the requirements for Ippatsu are fulfilled and the player wins by choosing a tile from the Option Tiles, Ippatsu is achieved.\n*If the player wins by choosing a tile after a Kan from the Option Tiles, After a Kan is achieved.\n* In the Duel of Divination mode, the Auto Draw&Discard function is disabled.","The Stargazing Trip event has started! Go to Event page - Planetarium to experience the new game mode Duel of Divination! You can earn Wishing Pts by playing Event Match or Ranked Match, read Rules for more information.","During the event, you can also complete missions in the Food Hall to get Wishing Pts.","When you have accumulated enough Wishing Pts, you can claim various rewards in the Wishmaking Garden.","Visit the Quaquaversal Movie Theatre to review the event stories.","Unlocks on 11/22 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Unlocks on 11/29 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Unlocks on {0}.","11/16 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/17 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/18 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/19 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/20 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/21 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/22 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/23 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/24