daily event missions to get gacha tokens (except matches played against AI).\nUse gacha tokens to pull for prizes in the machine!\n\n*You will get a prize with each gacha pull and the prizes will not return to the prize pool.\n*Pull 30 times to get the Special Prize.","Not enough gacha prizes left.","Go to Dorm to change outfit now?","Go to Dorm - Decoration?","Multiple Yakuman","Swap Calling allowed","Riichi with less than 4 tiles left","Double Wind Setting","Robbing a Closed Kan for Thirteen Orphans","Hand of Man Setting","Pay Responsibility Setting","Big Three Dragons & Four Big Winds","Big Three Dragons & Four Big Winds & Four Quads","2 Fu","4 Fu","","Limited-time available: Sakura Collab\n\nAside from collab-limited characters and collab-limited decorations, female characters and decorations available in Sakura Path can be summoned as well.","Limited-time available: Bamboo Collab\n\nAside from collab-limited characters and collab-limited decorations, male characters and decorations available in Bamboo Path can be summoned as well.","Great power should be used to protect what\'s important.\nGuard the Fortune tiles and challenge this exciting new game mode!","Special Rules: Operation Fortune Instructions\n\n- At the start of each round, the first 4 tiles that enter your hand are your Fortune tiles.\n- The Fortune tiles are revealed to all players.\n- Once a Fortune tile has been discarded, it becomes an ordinary tile and has no special effect anymore.\n- When a player wins, the number of Fortune tiles in their hand (including calls) can give the winning points additional bonus rates:\n-- 1 Fortune tile: Winning points x2\n-- 2 Fortune tile: Winning points x3\n-- 3 Fortune tile: Winning points x4\n-- 4 Fortune tile: Winning points x5\n\n*Players will see other players\' Fortune tiles placed at the right end of their hands.\n*Each player has their own set of Fortune tiles and they only come into effect at winning.\n*All players\' winning point rates will be displayed in real-time.\n*Fortune tiles do not affect No-ten Penalty, Round Bet, or Riichi Bet.\n*When a player makes a call, the Fortune tiles will be prioritized.\n\nAbout Event Pts\nDuring the event, play Ranked Match or Operation Fortune and you will get Event Pts as follows:\n4-Player: \n1st Place +200\n2nd Place +120\n3rd Place +60\n4th Place +20\n3-Player:\n1st Place +120\n2nd Place +60\n3rd Place +20\n\nWinning (Score below Mangan) +30\nWinning (Mangan) +60\nWinning (Haneman) +90\nWinning (Baiman) +120\nWinning (Sanbaiman) +180\nWinning (Yakuman and above) +240\n\nGame Mode: Operation Fortune - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","Special Rules: Operation Fortune Instructions\n\n- At the start of each round, the first 4 tiles that enter your hand are your Fortune tiles.\n- The Fortune tiles are revealed to all players.\n- Once a Fortune tile has been discarded, it becomes an ordinary tile and has no special effect anymore.\n- When a player wins, the number of Fortune tiles in their hand (including calls) can give the winning points additional bonus rates:\n-- 1 Fortune tile: Winning points x2\n-- 2 Fortune tile: Winning points x3\n-- 3 Fortune tile: Winning points x4\n-- 4 Fortune tile: Winning points x5\n\n*Players will see other players\' Fortune tiles placed at the right end of their hands.\n*Each player has their own set of Fortune tiles and they only come into effect at winning.\n*All players\' winning point rates will be displayed in real-time.\n*Fortune tiles do not affect No-ten Penalty, Round Bet, or Riichi Bet.\n*When a player makes a call, the Fortune tiles will be prioritized.","Truth of the Mask event has started! Go to Event page - Operation Fortune to experience the new event game mode! You can earn Event Pts by playing Event Match or Ranked Match, read Rules for more information.","During the event, you can also complete Event Missions to get Event Pts.","When you have accumulated enough Event Pts, you can claim various Milestone Rewards.","Go to Story Review to check out the event stories.","Unlocks on 5/3 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Unlocks on 5/10 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Unlocks on {0}.","4/26 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/27 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/28 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/29 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","4/30 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","5/1 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","5/2 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","5/3 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","5/4 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","5/5 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","5/6 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","5/7 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Operation Fortune","Claim All","Claimed","Matchmaking","Rules","Cancel Matchmaking","Accumulated Sign-in:","Day(s)","Tsumo Loss","Han Limit","Game SHA-256 Code:","Winning","Tablecloth","Music","Info loading failure","Info","Help","Empty","Show Owned","All","Regular - Sakura","Regular - Bamboo","Limited","Limited - Bamboo","Consume {0} Outfit Voucher(s) to get {0} Jade?\n*Jade cannot be converted to Outfit Vouchers.","Fortune Charm is in effect,\nclaim 10 Voting Tickets.","Vote for the outfit you want to see return!","After the end of the voting event, the Top 3 outfits for female characters and the Top 1 outfit for a male character will return during the next event.","With Fortune Charm in effect, \nget 10 Voting Tickets \n(1 time).","Select All","Deselect All","Tile Face","ATK","DEF","SPD","LUK","WIL","Summer Limited Event - Hand of Meow\nEvent Period: 8/15 - 9/8 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nIn this hot summer, One Han City is holding a daily tournament and Ichihime is here to participate!\nTo find the legendary Hand of Meow, Ichihime is training hard every day!\n\nDuring the event, complete missions to get limited tile back, limited tile face, event illustration, Summon Scrolls, and more!\n\nAbout Train\n- Ichihime has a max. Stamina of 100, each training session consumes 10 Stamina.\n- Complete daily event missions to gain extra Stamina, the portion of Stamina over the limit will remain.\n- Every day at 2 P.M. (UTC-7), Ichihime\'s Stamina will recharge to 100. (If it\'s already at max. or above, the Stamina will not change.)\n- Use different training methods to raise different stats for Ichihime.\n-- ATK will influence Ichihime\'s tendency for offense\n-- DEF will influence Ichihime\'s tendency for defense\n-- SPD will influence Ichihime\'s hand strategy choice\n-- LUK will affect Ichihime\'s chance for Hand of Meow\n-- WIL will affect Ichihime\'s fighting intent\n- When a stat reaches max. level, something mysterious might happen!\n\nAbout Battle\n- One Han City\'s Daily Tournament is open from 2:00 P.M. to the next day\'s 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7).\n- Aside from Ichihime, 7 other Jyanshis will participate in the tournament and they will fight to become that day\'s champion.\n- There are 4 rounds of matches every day, after all matches have finished, the total PT will determine that day\'s ranking.\n- When Ichihime wins the championship, something mysterious might happen!","{0}/{1} One Han City\'s Daily Tournament","Current Round:","Ichihime\'s Ranking:","{0}/{1}","Ichihime\'s Total PT: {0} Final Ranking: {1}","Ichihime\'s Total PT: {0} Tournament Unfinished","Round 1","Round 2","Round 3","Round 4","Ichihime is exhausted, nyaa...","Today\'s matches have all ended, please reenter the event page","Current round is ongoing","Current round has ended","Today\'s matches have ended","Unlock requirement: Ichihime winning the championship","Unlock requirement: One of Ichihime\'s stats reaching 999","=====Waiting for other matches in this round to end=====","=====Tidying up the mahjong table for the next round=====","Daily matches ended","Event ended.","Streamer Mode","Show","Hide","Player names and notes in Friend List & Friendly Match are hidden.","Player names from other servers","In-match player names from same server","Player names in Log","Player names in Watch","Player names in Tournament Match","Player names in Rank","Unlocks on 9/27 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Unlocks on 9/28 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Unlocks on 9/29 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Unlocks on 9/30 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Unlocked","Locked","*Read any story chapter of the day to get rewards.","Day1","Day2","Day3","Day4","Day5","The Autumn Wind Blows Event\nEvent Period: 9/26 - 10/10 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\n- During the event, accumulate winning points in matches (except matches played against AI), and get 1 Siver Fox for every 10,000 winning points accumulated (max. 4).\n\n- As One Han City has yet to acquire the Time Skip function, new story chapters will unlock as time passes.\n\n- Whether life gets exciting or remains peaceful is sometimes determined by the smallest change of mind as your choices will decide the outcome of the story. But don\'t worry about making the wrong choice, this cute Silver Fox has the power to take you to another storyline.\n\n- Friendly reminder, don\'t forget to check if there are unclaimed rewards as all enthusiastic citizens of One Han City deserve them.","To be unlocked soon.","Unlock with Silver Fox*1 after you reach one ending on Day 1.","Unlock with Silver Fox*1 after you finish reading the story of the previous day.","Unlocks after you reach one ending on Day 1.","Unlocks after you finish reading the story of the previous day.","Successfully unlocked.","Consecutive\nDraw Discard: {0}","Consecutive\nHand Discard: {0}","1 Daily Quest will be updated every day.","2 Daily Quests will be updated every day.","Holy Mahjong War","Battle of Incantation","Holy Mahjong War event has started! Go to Event page - Battle of Incantation to experience the new event game mode! You can earn Event Pts by playing Event Match or Ranked Match, read Rules for more information.","During the event, you can also complete Event Missions to get Mana.","When you have accumulated enough Mana, you can claim various Magical Rewards.","Go to Story Review to check out the event stories.","Special Rules: Battle of Incantation Instructions\n\n- In this mode, when you draw a tile and discard it directly (Draw Discard), this tile will be shown darkened among the discarded tiles.\n- When you draw a tile and discard a tile from your hand (Hand Discard), this tile will be shown like usual among the discarded tiles.\n- Among your discarded tiles, when you achieve 3 or more consecutive Draw Discards or Hand Discards, you get added Han Bonus when you win.\n-- When you achieve 3/5/7/9/12 consecutive Draw Discards, you will be rewarded with 1/2/3/5/12 additional Han (Crimson Bonus).\n-- When you achieve 3/6/9/12/18 consecutive Hand Discards, you will be rewarded with 1/2/3/5/12 additional Han (Azure Bonus).\n*When you achieve consecutive Draw Discards multiple times, the highest number will be used for the bonus count.\n*When you achieve consecutive Hand Discards multiple times, the highest number will be used for the bonus count.\n*Han Bonus of all players will be displayed next to the players\' avatars in real-time.\n*Crimson and Azure are not Yaku, they only affect Han count after you win.\n*When a player wins, both Crimson and Azure Bonus will be counted when calculating the winning points.\n\n\nAbout Mana\nDuring the event, play Ranked Match or Battle of Incantation and you will get Mana as follows:\n4-Player: \n1st Place +200\n2nd Place +120\n3rd Place +60\n4th Place +20\n3-Player:\n1st Place +120\n2nd Place +60\n3rd Place +20\n\nWinning (Score below Mangan) +30\nWinning (Mangan) +60\nWinning (Haneman) +90\nWinning (Baiman) +120\nWinning (Sanbaiman) +180\nWinning (Yakuman and above) +240\n\nGame Mode: Battle of Incantation - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","Special Rules: Battle of Incantation Instructions\n\n- In this mode, when you draw a tile and discard it directly (Draw Discard), this tile will be shown darkened among the discarded tiles.\n- When you draw a tile and discard a tile from your hand (Hand Discard), this tile will be shown like usual among the discarded tiles.\n- Among your discarded tiles, when you achieve 3 or more consecutive Draw Discards or Hand Discards, you get added Han Bonus when you win.\n-- When you achieve 3/5/7/9/12 consecutive Draw Discards, you will be rewarded with 1/2/3/5/12 additional Han (Crimson Bonus).\n-- When you achieve 3/6/9/12/18 consecutive Hand Discards, you will be rewarded with 1/2/3/5/12 additional Han (Azure Bonus).\n*When you achieve consecutive Draw Discards multiple times, the highest number will be used for the bonus count.\n*When you achieve consecutive Hand Discards multiple times, the highest number will be used for the bonus count.\n*Han Bonus of all players will be displayed next to the players\' avatars in real-time.\n*Crimson and Azure are not Yaku, they only affect Han count after you win.\n*When a player wins, both Crimson and Azure Bonus will be counted when calculating the winning points.","See through the river of tiles where light and dark are intertwined, and chant the magic of crimson and azure!\nChoose your spell carefully and challenge this exciting new 4-Player East game mode!","11/15\n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/16\n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/17\n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/18\n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/19\n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/20\n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/21 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/22 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/23 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/24 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/25 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11/29 \n2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","11월 20일 \n06:00 AM(GMT+9)","11월 25일 \n06:00 AM(GMT+9)","11월 30일 \n06:00 AM(GMT+9)","Nothing here, nyaa.","Mana: {0}","Ended","You have served all customers today!","Undo","Unlocks at {0} Praise PT","Unlocks at\n{0} Praise PT","Claim All","Daily Missions will be refreshed at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7) every day.","You can also get Red Panda Coins by playing matches with no AI (the number depends\non your winning points). For more information, please check out the event details.","Winter Exclusive Event - Yuzu\'s Kitchen\nEvent Period: 12/19 -1/8 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nA new restaurant suddenly appeared on One Han City\'s commercial strip.\nAnd when it opens, the owner of the place is revealed to be... Yuzu and her Red Panda Squad!\nWith how busy and chaotic it is, what they need now is the help of someone trustworthy!\n\nDuring the event, complete the customers\' orders to receive praise and get rewards including the new Tile Call Indicator, Event Illustration, Summon Scroll, and more!\n\nAbout Orders\n- Every day at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7), a certain number of customers will arrive at Yuzu\'s Kitchen and announce their preference for the day.\n- Complete the orders to the customers\' satisfaction, receive Praise PT, and get various rewards!\n\nAbout Food\n- During the event, complete Daily Missions to get Red Panda Coins.\n- Play matches with no AI, you will also get Red Panda Coins when you win a game.\nWinning (Score below Mangan) +30\nWinning (Mangan) +60\nWinning (Haneman) +90\nWinning (Baiman) +120\nWinning (Sanbaiman) +180\nWinning (Yakuman and above) +240\n- Tap the food tray on the right, Red Panda Coins will be consumed and new food will appear on the table.\n- Each food tray will only give you one of the two foods shown.\n\nAbout Synthesis\n- The food on the table can be used to synthesize other food or fulfill orders.\n- Drag two identical foods together to synthesize a higher-level food of the same category.\n- Food of the highest level cannot be used for synthesis.\n- Tap Recipes to check out the Synthesis Recipes.\n\nAbout Tips\n- Every time you synthesize, there is a chance that Tips may appear.\n- Drag Tips to Recycle and you will get Praise PT directly!\n- You can also synthesize Tips of higher level and exchange them for more Praise PT.\n- 10 Tips will appear at most each day.\n\nAbout Recycle\n- You can drag any food you don\'t need to Recycle, and you will receive Red Panda Coins in return,\n- You will lose a proportion of the food\'s value in Recycle, so tread carefully!\n- If there is no other action taken in between, you can Undo the last Recycle action (except Tips).\n\nYuzu\'s Notice\n- Check out the customers\' orders first before choosing a food tray!\n- Avoid wasting food is a must-learn lesson for all Friends of Justice!","Unlocks on {0}.","12/20 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/21 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/22 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/23 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/24 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/25 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/26 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/27 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/28 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/29 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/30 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","12/31 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","1/1 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","The table is full, please make place on the table first.","You don\'t have sufficient coins.","Fortune Charm Effect:","Day(s)","Claiming...","Mahjong Soul has stopped supporting creating new accounts with X (previously Twitter). Please use another method.","Mahjong Soul has stopped supporting login with X (previously Twitter). Please use another method.","You have served all the customers!","Unlocks at {0} PT","Mine","Field","Forest","Expedition","Cottage","Missions","Apple Orchard","Pear Orchard","Orange Orchard","Offer Up","Level Up","Destination","Lv.","Go","In Expedition","Prosperity:{0}","+{0}/harvest","1/30 - 2/19 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","Produced materials will be \ncollected at every harvest season.","Next Harvest:","Repair the broken stairs at the entrance","The newly arrived potted plants are a bit monotonous and need some embellishment","Fruits are out of stock, let\'s get more","The chair creaks, let\'s get a new one","Put a fruit basket here for the aroma of fruits","Change the plaque to one that better represents the White Dragon","Red lanterns should be hung to celebrate the New Year","The living room needs a new coffee table for the fruits","Please wait","Hmm, I\'m still considering, I\'ll let you know in {0} day(s).","Level Up Successful!","Insufficient material","Insufficient cottage space","Max level reached","No idle Dragonling\nComplete White Dragon\'s Requests to get more Dragonlings","No idle Dragonling","No empty slot","Idle Dragonling available","When there is not enough wheat for every dragonling, all dragonlings will go on strike together and stop production. \nSend more dragonlings to the field, reduce the number of working dragonlings, get more wheat from completing matches with no AI are all effective ways to prevent strikes.","Insufficient wheat","Insufficient wheat soon","(Sent: {0})","Idle Dragonling(s): {0}","Request Completed!","Oh, Master, you\'ve come! Maybe it\'s due to the call of the Year of Dragon, a White Dragon has descended upon this village, nyaa!","The White Dragon also has a group of Dragonlings as her servants, but as far as Ichihime gathered, they are not hostile, and they say they will help rebuild the village as long as food is provided!","(Hopefully they don\'t intend to keep the whole village for their own comfort, nyaa...)","The village consists of several areas that produce different materials.","Like this one is the forest, nyaa! Based on Ichihime\'s knowledge, this place should produce wood, nyaa!\nLet\'s tap on an empty slot and send a Dragonling to work here!","Yes, just like that, nyaa! The Dragonling is now working diligently.\nAt the next harvest season, you will get the wood this Dragonling collected, nyaa!","Reasonable distribution of labor is the secret to prosperity and development, nyaa!\nLet\'s tap and discharge this Dragonling and find a more suitable work for it.","Well done, now you get the hang of being a leader, as expected of Master, nyaa!\nNow this Dragonling is waiting for orders in the cottage.\nYou can decide where it should work afterwards, nyaa!","More Dragonlings means more workers, nyaa!\nLet\'s tap on the White Dragon Temple and visit the White Dragon, maybe we will get more Dragonlings!","So this is where the White Dragon lives, nyaa!\nIt looks more extravagant than the cottage where the Dragonlings are staying...","Offer up materials the White Dragon demands to complete the requests, and more Dragonlings will arrive!","Congratulations, nyaa! Our village revival team has added another capable member.\nLet\'s leave the White Dragon Temple and return to the village.","That\'s about everything you need to know. If there\'s anything you are not sure about, tap the Help button anytime to check out the rules.\nIchihime will go check on the orchard and report back to Master later, nyaa!","(I wonder what magically ripened fruits taste like, nyaa...)","Expedition Complete","Offer up 20 apples to the White Dragon","Offer up 20 pears to the White Dragon","Offer up 20 oranges to the White Dragon","Offer up 20 wood to help repair the White Dragon Temple","Offer up 20 stones to help repair the White Dragon Temple","Unlocks at Prosperity {0}","Extra Coppers Gained: {0}","Spring Festival Event - White Dragon\'s Wish\nEvent Time: 1/30 - 2/19 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nSummoned by the Year of Dragon, in a temple in the outer suburbs of One Han City, an actual White Dragon appeared!\nThe White Dragon looked down on the village with an arrogant gaze, and summons a group of diligent and hardworking Dragonlings who only slack off occasionally.\nWhen the White Dragon\'s wishes are fulfilled, the village will surely be revitalized, nyaa!\n\nDuring the event, collect materials, raise the prosperity of the village, and get various rewards including match music, Summon Scroll, event illustration, Spring Festival emote, and more!\n\nAbout Village and Harvest\n- The village is composed of various areas, send Dragonlings to work in the areas to get corresponding materials at harvest seasons.\nForest produces wood;\nMine produces stones;\nOrchard produces fruits;\nField produces wheat.\n- When an area is leveled up, work slots will be added.\n- Use Harvest Power to skip to the next harvest season, and the result of this harvest will be settled, consuming wheat first and producing materials afterwards.\n- Harvest Power can be obtained via completing daily missions.\n- Tap the materials to collect them.\n- Unclaimed materials will not disappear during the event period, and there\'s no capacity limit either.\n\nAbout Production and Consumption\n- Production Efficiency\nFor each Dragonling working in forest, mine and orchard, corresponding material*1 is produced per harvest.\nFor each Dragonling working in the field, wheat*4 is produced per harvest.\n(Even when no Dragonling is in the field, wheat*1 is produced per harvest.)\n- Product Consumption\nEvery working Dragonling consumes wheat*1 per harvest.\n\nAbout Dragonlings\n- Dragonlings are the White Dragon\'s most loyal servants, complete White Dragon\'s Requests to get more dragonlings.\n- Tap on empty slots in any area to assign idle Dragonlings to go work there.\n- Tap on a working Dragonling in any area to let it go rest in the cottage.\n- Each Dragonling needs its own space in the cottage.\n- Level up the cottage for more empty space.\n\nAbout Strikes\n- When harvest season arrives, and there is not enough wheat for every dragonling, all dragonlings will go on strike together and stop production.\n- Send more dragonlings to the field, reduce the number of working dragonlings, get more wheat from matches with no AI are all effective ways to prevent strikes.\n\nAbout White Dragon\'s Requests\n- Complete White Dragon\'s Requests to get more Dragonlings.\n- When Prosperity reaches 100, special requests that can be completed repeatedly will be unlocked, complete them to get Coppers.\n\nAbout Fruits and Expedition\n- Every village will only grow one of three fruits.\n- To get other fruits, you need to send Dragonlings on expeditions to other villages.\n- The destinations of the expeditions are the players\' villages on your friend list. The amount of fruits you get from each expedition depends on the orchard level of that player.\n- Each expedition needs 1 Dragonling and lasts 3 harvest seasons.\n- The wheat needed for the expedition will be consumed before it starts.\n\nAbout Prosperity\n- Higher Prosperity will bring change to the White Dragon.\n- When Prosperity reaches 100, special requests that can be completed repeatedly will be unlocked, complete them to get Coppers.\n- For each Dragonling, Prosperity +3\n- For each area at Lv.1, Prosperity +1\n- For each area at Lv.2, Prosperity +3\n- For each area at Lv.3, Prosperity +6\n- For each area at Lv.4, Prosperity +11\n- For each cottage upgrade, Prosperity +1\n\nIchihime\'s Reminder\n- Master, don\'t worry, due to the peculiarity of the village, unclaimed materials will not disappear, nyaa.\n- Anything that happens in the village that looks inexplicable, is surely due to the White Dragon\'s powers, nyaa!\n- Once Prosperity reaches 100, you can exchange fruits for more Coppers, as the White Dragon loves fruits, nyaa!\n- Along with the rise of Prosperity in the village, the White Dragon in the temple might undergo unexpected changes, nyaa...","Repeat Requests","MAX","Dragonlings are on strike: not enough food!","Clear out the weeds in the courtyard","-{0}/harvest","Idle Dragonlings do not consume food.Complete White Dragon\'s Requests to get more Dragonlings","- Higher Prosperity will bring change to the White Dragon.\n- When Prosperity reaches 100, special requests that can be completed repeatedly will be unlocked, complete them to get Coppers.\n- For each Dragonling, Prosperity +3\n- For each area at Lv.1, Prosperity +1\n- For each area at Lv.2, Prosperity +3\n- For each area at Lv.3, Prosperity +6\n- For each area at Lv.4, Prosperity +11\n- For each cottage upgrade, Prosperity +1","{0}min","White Dragon\'s Rewards","{0}s","Complete a match with no AI to get Wheat x{0}.","Today\'s Wheat gain from matches: {0}","Tutorial","Work Time:","{0}d","{0}harvest(s)","Expedition Time: {0} harvests.\nThe amount of fruits you will get from an expedition is determined by the destination village\'s orchard level.","Insufficient event time remaining to complete expedition","Returns after \n{0} harvest seasons","1/31 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/1 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/2 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/3 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/4 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/5 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/6 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/7 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/8 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/9 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/10 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/11 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","2/12 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","There are still idle Dragonlings in the cottage, skip to the next harvest season anyway?","You don\'t have enough Wheat now, you can complete matches with no AI to get more Wheat.\nBy the next harvest season, each working Dragonling will consume 1 Wheat.","Remaining:","Skip to Harvest","Insufficient Harvest Power, you cannot enter the next harvest season.\nComplete daily missions to get more Harvest Power.","Complete White Dragon\'s Requests to get more Dragonlings","Speaking of which, the White Dragon in the temple is really powerful, nyaa...\nShe can give you Harvest Power to accelerate the time in the village, nyaa!!","Though Ichihime is doubtful... But Master, let\'s try it out first, nyaa!\nTap the button and skip to the next harvest season! (First try provided by the White Dragon for free)","Harvest Power... is actually real! The wood is produced in a blink of an eye, nyaa!\nI\'ll take them this time, Master, and next time you can claim them yourself by tapping on the bubble, nyaa!","A stone path in front of the gate makes it easier to walk in and out","The bathing corner needs an exquisite folding screen","Build an elegant and scenic garden","The White Dragon Temple needs a second floor","My servants are working hard, get them some fruits as rewards","The temple needs a complete set of customized furniture","harvest(s)","Special Rules: Operation Fortune Instructions\n\n- At the start of each round, the first 4 tiles that enter your hand are your Fortune tiles.\n- The Fortune tiles are revealed to all players.\n- Once a Fortune tile has been discarded, it becomes an ordinary tile and has no special effect anymore.\n- When a player wins, the number of Fortune tiles in their hand (including calls) can give the winning points additional bonus rates:\n-- 1 Fortune tile: Winning points x2\n-- 2 Fortune tile: Winning points x3\n-- 3 Fortune tile: Winning points x4\n-- 4 Fortune tile: Winning points x5\n\n*Players will see other players\' Fortune tiles placed at the right end of their hands.\n*Each player has their own set of Fortune tiles and they only come into effect at winning.\n*All players\' winning point rates will be displayed in real-time.\n*Fortune tiles do not affect No-ten Penalty, Round Bet, or Riichi Bet.\n*When a player makes a call, the Fortune tiles will be prioritized.\n\nGame Mode: Operation Fortune - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60\nBond Point Bonus: 40\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","Special Rules: Battle of Incantation Instructions\n\n- In this mode, when you draw a tile and discard it directly (Draw Discard), this tile will be shown darkened among the discarded tiles.\n- When you draw a tile and discard a tile from your hand (Hand Discard), this tile will be shown like usual among the discarded tiles.\n- Among your discarded tiles, when you achieve 3 or more consecutive Draw Discards or Hand Discards, you get added Han Bonus when you win.\n-- When you achieve 3/5/7/9/12 consecutive Draw Discards, you will be rewarded with 1/2/3/5/12 additional Han (Crimson Bonus).\n-- When you achieve 3/6/9/12/18 consecutive Hand Discards, you will be rewarded with 1/2/3/5/12 additional Han (Azure Bonus).\n*When you achieve consecutive Draw Discards multiple times, the highest number will be used for the bonus count.\n*When you achieve consecutive Hand Discards multiple times, the highest number will be used for the bonus count.\n*Han Bonus of all players will be displayed next to the players\' avatars in real-time.\n*Crimson and Azure are not Yaku, they only affect Han count after you win.\n*When a player wins, both Crimson and Azure Bonus will be counted when calculating the winning points.\n\nGame Mode: Battle of Incantation - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","Starting Points: 50,000\nExtension into South: At the end of 4th East game, if 1st place has less than 55,000 points\nLength: East Round Match\nRed Five: 3\nOpen Tanyao: On\nWaiting Time: 5+20","Starting Points: 25,000\nExtension into South: At the end of 4th East game, if 1st place has less than 30,000 points\nLength: East Round Match\nRed Five: 3\nOpen Tanyao: On\nWaiting Time: 5+20","Sign Up","Login","HIBI CHANNEL","[3.19 - 4.2 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)]","Follow","Followed","Owned: {0}","{0} x{1}","Gift","Popularity","K","Insufficient {0}","Live","At Popularity","Get Gifts","Hibiki Himekawa\'s Channel - LIVE NOW!\nEvent Period: 3.19 - 4.2 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nDuring the event, log in and complete event missions daily to get event items.\nGift these event items in Hibiki\'s channel to interact with her and increase the Popularity of her channel.\nWhen the channel\'s Popularity reaches certain milestones, you will get Fan Rewards, including Event Limited BGM, Event Illustration, Sage\'s Bag and more!\n\n*Matches played against AI do not count towards event missions.\n*Event Illustration may be added to Shop - Illustration in the future.","Change","Fes Proposal","Event-limited item.","School Fes Frenzy event item, contains the passion and expactation of the applicants. Approving proposals will affect Fes Stats. Obtainable via completing Festival Missions or spending Fes Budget on the Member Management page.","Soul Punch","Special Rules: Soul Punch\n\n- Riichi is considered a 2 Han Yaku, and Double Riichi a 3 Han Yaku.\n- When a player declares Riichi, they gain Soul Punch status for 6 turns.\n- When Soul Punch is active, the player continues Auto Draw and Discard, and the other players\' turns are skipped.\n- When Soul Punch is active, Tsumo is considered achieving Ippatsu.\n- When Soul Punch is active, and a discarded is called by any other player, Soul Punch ends.\n- The player losing the Soul Punch status receives the Weak debuff.\n- When a player deals in with the Weak debuff, the winning hand gains an extra 2 Han.\n\n*If the Riichi discard tile is called by any other player, the Soul Punch status ends directly.\n*When Soul Punch is active, calling a Closed Kan also counts towards the Soul Punch counter.\n*When the player calls a Closed Kan while the Soul Punch counter reaches 0, the Soul Punch status extends to when the player discards the tile to complete the Kan call and ends after this discard.\n*If multiple deal-ins happen to a player under the Weak debuff, all winning hands gain an extra 2 Han.\n\nGame Mode: Soul Punch - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","Special Rules: Soul Punch\n\n- Riichi is considered a 2 Han Yaku, and Double Riichi a 3 Han Yaku.\n- When a player declares Riichi, they gain Soul Punch status for 6 turns.\n- When Soul Punch is active, the player continues Auto Draw and Discard, and the other players\' turns are skipped.\n- When Soul Punch is active, Tsumo is considered achieving Ippatsu.\n- When Soul Punch is active, and a discarded is called by any other player, Soul Punch ends.\n- The player losing the Soul Punch status receives the Weak debuff.\n- When a player deals in with the Weak debuff, the winning hand gains an extra 2 Han.\n\n*If the Riichi discard tile is called by any other player, the Soul Punch status ends directly.\n*When Soul Punch is active, calling a Closed Kan also counts towards the Soul Punch counter.\n*When the player calls a Closed Kan while the Soul Punch counter reaches 0, the Soul Punch status extends to when the player discards the tile to complete the Kan call and ends after this discard.\n*If multiple deal-ins happen to a player under the Weak debuff, all winning hands gain an extra 2 Han.","Unlocks in {0} day(s)","Unlocks in {0} hour(s)","Unlocks in {0} minute(s)","Refreshes in {0} day(s)","Refreshes in {0} hour(s)","Refreshes in {0} minute(s)","Ending","Complete matches with no AI to get \nFes Budget x{0}","Fes Rank","UP!!","Unlock Incident x{0}","Rank Up \nRequirement","Festival Missions","Club Rewards","Garden of Memories","Member Management","Mahjong Clubroom","Festival Proposal Form","Applicant:","Proposal","Insufficient Fes Budget! Complete Festival Missions and approve proposals to get more Fes Budget!","Great Success","Success","Failure","Matchmaking","Member Level Up","Lv.{0}","Level Up","Unlocks in {0} day(s)","Unlocks at Fes Rank {0}","Lv.MAX","Procure Proposal","Insufficient Fes Budget! Complete Festival Missions and approve proposals to get more Fes Budget!","Procurable today\n{0}/{1}","You have reached today\'s limit. Please come back tomorrow for more proposals.","Skill Activated!","Failures have a certain chance of becoming Success!","Special Rules: Soul Punch\n\n- Riichi is considered a 2 Han Yaku, and Double Riichi a 3 Han Yaku.\n- When a player declares Riichi, they gain Soul Punch status for 6 turns.\n- When Soul Punch is active, the player continues Auto Draw and Discard, and the other players\' turns are skipped.\n- When Soul Punch is active, Tsumo is considered achieving Ippatsu.\n- When Soul Punch is active, and a discarded is called by any other player, Soul Punch ends.\n- The player losing the Soul Punch status receives the Weak debuff.\n- When a player deals in with the Weak debuff, the winning hand gains an extra 2 Han.\n\n*If the Riichi discard tile is called by any other player, the Soul Punch status ends directly.\n*When Soul Punch is active, calling a Closed Kan also counts towards the Soul Punch counter.\n*When the player calls a Closed Kan while the Soul Punch counter reaches 0, the Soul Punch status extends to when the player discards the tile to complete the Kan call and ends after this discard.\n*If multiple deal-ins happen to a player under the Weak debuff, all winning hands gain an extra 2 Han.\n\nGame Mode: Soul Punch - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1000 Coppers\nGames played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60","Declaring war fearlessly even in the face of weakness, strike this Soul Punch with all your might!\nPlay this super exciting 4-Player East game!","Weekly Festival Missions","Claim","Progress","Refreshes every week at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7) on Tuesday","Incomplete","Check>","Collab Limited Event - School Fes Frenzy!\nEvent Period: 4/16 - 5/7 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nThe Asaha High School Festival is in full swing. However, with how busy it is, the school is short-staffed and needs your help! \nWork together with some special members to strategize for the festival!\n\nDuring the event, approve proposals and raise Fes Rank to get Summon Scroll, Illustration, and other rewards!\n\nAbout Proposals\n- Approving proposals will affect Fes Stats (positively and negatively). Each arrow stands for 10pt.\n- How much Fes Stats increase or decrease will be affected by the result of the approved proposals, and some member skills can affect their success rate!\n- Proposals can be obtained by completing Festival Missions.\n- After raising the level of certain members, you can also procure proposals on the Member Management page.\n\nAbout Fes Rank\n- Fes Rank is linked to the three Fes Stats, Education, Fun, and Safety.\n- When the Fes Stats meet the Rank Up Requirement, the Fes Rank will go up and more rewards will be unlocked.\n\nAbout Incidents\n- When the Fes Rank goes up, some special incidents will occur and completing them will increase the Fes Stats greatly!\n- Depending on your decision, Festival Incidents will have different outcomes.\n\nAbout Members\n- Each member has their own skill, and you can use Fes Budget to level up Members and enhance their skills.\n- Some Member Skills will only be unlocked when you have reached a certain Fes Rank.\n- You can get Fes Budget by completing Festival Missions or completing matches with no AI.\n\nIchihime\'s Reminder\n- Complete any match with no AI to get Fes Budget x10.\n- The exchange rate of winning points from Ranked Match or Soul Punch: 4-player match: 1:1, 3-player match: 3:1.\n- Using Fes Budget wisely is the key to managing the proposals.\n- Don\'t worry about the proposals that are rejected, Ichihime will placate the applicants, nyaa!","Close","Well done!","Something went wrong...","To Be Approved: {0}","You\'ve gotten a mountain of\nproposals to deal with...","Procurement \nsuccessful!","Level up Aru\nto unlock","→","Bonus Rewards","Complete Festival Missions to get Proposals","Let\'s give it our all today too!","Check Proposal","Check Result","Stats Reward x2","Ends in {0} day(s)","Ends in {0} hour(s)","Ends in {0} minute(s)","Sign-in","Weekly Quests","You have completed all the other quests!","Master, Asaha High School is holding a school festival, with lots of fun activities and delicious food, nyaa...\nBut they are short of manpower, so they ask if Master can help out with approving proposals, nyaa!","(Ichihime has already said yes and ate the pudding, so Master can\'t say no, nyaa...)","Nyaa nyaa? We alreadt got a proposal here!\nMaster, let\'s tap on this proposal and check out the content, nyaa!","Kaguyahime","I propose we forbid Ichihime to take part in the festival, she has already cleared the stock of the snack stand at the school gate on her own.","Agree","Strongly Agree","M-Master, don\'t take this prank seriously, nyaa!!\n...Anyways, when you approve a proposal, the three Fes Stats will change, nyaa!","When the Fes Stats meet the rank up requirement, the Fes Rank will go up.\nThe current rank is E-, so we still have a long way to go... But I\'m sure Master can do it, nyaa!","The good news is that Master won\'t be working alone, nyaa.\nA few special guests have appeared at the festival and they will help you out, nyaa!","Let\'s go meet them now.\nTap here to go to Member Management, nyaa.","Different members have different skills, \nand you can use Fes Budget to level up Members and enhance their skills, nyaa.","You can use extra Fes Budget to procure more proposals by asking Aru for help.\nDon\'t forget to use this method, nyaa.","That\'s everything Ichihime knows, and you can tap the ? button on the upper right corner for more details.\nWith Master\'s help, I\'m sure this school festival will be a big success, nyaa!","(I only have so much space in my stomach but there\'s so many snacks, what should I do, nyaa...)","Waits","Show Waits","Show Hands","Mode Introduction","Detailed Rules","Traditional Riichi Mahjong Rules\nYou can adjust the specifics in advanced settings","Blessed by Mahjong Soul Shrine, this charm will be the source of your fortune.","Go to Download","Go to Official Website","Fortune Charm(30d) Obtained","Double to pass & discard","Ichihime\'s Backpack","Kaguyahime\'s Backpack","Wanjirou\'s Backpack","Pier","Bakery","Island School","Mahjong Zone","Holiday Resort","SAMU Joy Island","Current Location","Today\'s Market Price","Locked","Refreshes at 2:00 \nP.M. (UTC-7)","Go","Acquire {0} Island Coins to unlock","({0}%)","Enter","Not enough Fresh Coconut Juice in stock, so the helpers are unwilling to keep working. Complete daily missions to get more Fresh Coconut Juice.","Summer Limited Event - Summer on Joy Island\nEvent Period: 6/25 - 7/16 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nOne Han City\'s famous Samu Corporation has just completed the construction of the island amusement park SAMU Joy Island, which will soon start a 21-day soft opening.\nNot only are there amusement rides on the island, but it seems there are also plenty of business opportunities waiting for you to discover!\n\nDuring the event, trade goods, earn more Island Coins, and you can obtain rich rewards such as limited Tile Back, Summon Scroll, and Event Illustrations!\n\nAbout the Island\n- The island consists of 6 areas: SAMU Joy Island, Holiday Resort, Mahjong Zone, Island School, Bakery, and Pier.\n- SAMU Joy Island allows you to view the Summer Memories story.\n- SAMU Joy Island and the other four areas are connected by roads, and you can move between the areas by consuming the event item Fresh Coconut Juice.\n- Areas that are locked require more Island Coins to unlock before you can visit.\n- Fresh Coconut Juice can be obtained by completing daily missions.\n\nAbout Markets\n- There is a market each in the Holiday Resort, Mahjong Zone, Island School, Bakery, and Pier.\n- The markets refresh several goods and their corresponding market prices every day at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7).\n- When buying and selling goods in the market, you need to pay the current market price.\n- After adding goods to the Shopping Cart, you need to pack them in the Backpack before you can check out and take them away.\n\nAbout Backpack\n- The Backpack consists of several slots, which can hold goods of different shapes.\nYou can spend Island Coins to unlock more Backpack slots to carry more and larger goods!\n- If you have enough Island Coins, Kaguyahime and Wanjirou should also be willing to come over and help, nyaa!\n\nAbout Island News\n- Something new happens on the island every day, which will significantly affect the prices of goods in the markets the next day.\n- The news refreshes promptly at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7) every day, remember to check the news often, nyaa!\n\nIchihime\'s Tips\n- Ichihime thinks that as long as you follow the principle of buying when the price drops and selling when the price rises, you can steadfastly make money, nyaa!\n- Since the customer is God, placing items randomly in the market is allowed.\n- There are many Empty Bottles at the Pier that can be bought very cheaply, which is also a good way to earn start-up funds, nyaa.\n- Ichihime reserves the final interpretation right on how to spend the earned Island Coins.","Merchant\'s Island Coins, which will determine if the merchant can afford your goods. Resets every day at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7).","Sort by Price","Sort by Price Change","Goods","Market Price","On Sale","Owned","Average Cost","Average Cost: The average price of Island Coins spent when purchasing the item (only calculated for items in the backpack).\nWhen the Average Cost is less than the market\'s purchase price, it indicates a profit when selling the item.","Sell","None","Shopping Cart","Check Out","Tips","There are unpacked item(s) in the Shopping Cart, only check out the item(s) packed in your Backpack?","After checkout, the remaining item(s) in the Shopping Cart will be returned to the shelf.","Check Out","Pack Again","Market Purchase Price: {0}","Current Average Cost: {0}","The Purchase Price is {0}% of the Market Price","You found Kaguyahime who is having a sunbath at the moment. Looks like you can ask her to help carry goods. But you have to have [tag]{0}[/tag]/{1} Island Coins for her to be willing to help.","You found Wanjirou who is devouring some seafood ramen at the moment. Looks like you can ask him to help carry goods. But you have to have [tag]{0}[/tag]/{1} Island Coins for him to be willing to help.","See you later!","Deal!","New Helper Unlocked","You have more Backpack space now","New Area Unlocked","You can explore more areas now","Team Backpack",