 your hand, you can call Pon on any tile discarded by other players.","","","","","Dora is not a Yaku, it only adds to your Han count after winning.","","","","","Seat Wind and Prevalent Wind are both East, so the Triplet of East tiles is a Yaku here.","","","","","Get either 4 Pin or 7 Pin, and you have a winning hand!","Wrong answer, think again, nyaa!","Read today\'s question carefully, nyaa!","Complete all 7 days\' missions to get:","","","","Welcome to Mahjong Soul Shrine! Are you here for fun times playing mahjong as well? Let\'s learn the basic rules of mahjong first!","Mahjong has 34 different tiles, and they can be sorted into 5 groups: [tag]Man, Pin, Sou, Wind, and Dragon[/tag]. There are 4 of each tile, so in total there are 136 tiles.","Sequence: 3 consecutive number tiles of the same group\nTriplet: 3 identical tiles\nPair: 2 identical tiles","The main objective of mahjong is complete a winning hand. Usually, it means the player has to achieve a hand consisting of [tag]4 Sequences/Triplets + 1 Pair[/tag]!","To reach that goal, each turn, you draw 1 tile from the tile wall and if it\'s not the winning tile, you choose 1 tile to discard and maintain a hand consisting of 13 tiles. Step by step, you will get closer to a winning hand.","Here, let\'s discard the West tile that\'s unneeded here.","In addition to the tile group requirement, to win, the winning hand must also contain at least 1 [tag]Yaku[/tag].","Now I want to introduce a really popular and easily achievable Yaku: [tag]All Simples[/tag], also called Tanyao! If your hand only has number tiles with numbers from 2 to 8, in other words, does not have Honor tiles (Wind or Dragon tiles), or Terminal tiles (number tiles with 1/9), then it meets the requirement for All Simples. Let\'s try it out!","We already have 1 Triplet, 2 Sequences, and 1 Pair, so once we have completed the last Sequence, we have a winning hand! And it meets the requirement for All Simples!","When your hand is waiting for the winning tile like this, you are in [tag]Tenpai[/tag]. If you have Yaku and are in Tenpai, you just need someone to discard the last needed tile or draw it yourself to win.","That\'s the tile we need! We can win now, tap the [tag]Ron[/tag] button!","The red mark on the table has moved! That means the dealer seated East has changed!","This is an East Wind match, so the match ends when every player has been dealer 1 time, don\'t think of running away before the match ends!","When the match ends, the 4 players will be ranked from 1st to 4th. Do your best and aim for 1st place!","The \"East 2\" in the center indicates that the match is at the 2nd game of the East Wind Round. East Wind is the current Prevalent Wind. X 69 indicates the number of tiles remaining. If this number becomes 0, then this game will end even if no one wins.","The \"W\" in front of you indicates you are seated West in this game, and West is your Seat Wind.","[tag]A Triplet of Prevalent Wind[/tag] and [tag]a Triplet of Seat Wind[/tag] are both very common Yakus. If you get 3 West tiles, then you can win with Seat Wind - West as Yaku.","If [tag]any other player[/tag] discards a tile and you have 2 tiles of the same kind in your hand, you can call [tag]Pon[/tag] to form a Triplet. Upon calling Pon, you shall openly place the Triplet formed in the corner of your table.","Now! Don\'t miss this tile, tap the Pon button!","After you called Pon successfully, discard 1 tile from your hand.","If [tag]the player on your left discards[/tag] a tile that can form a Sequence with 2 tiles in your hand, you can call [tag]Chii[/tag] on that tile. Upon calling Chii, you shall openly place the Sequence formed in the corner of your table.","You can call Chii on this tile, tap the Chii button!","After you called Chii successfully, discard 1 tile from your hand too, nyaa.","Now you reached Tenpai. When you draw 1 Pin or 4 Pin yourself or someone else discards either tile, you win.","If you have 4 of the same tile, you can tap [tag]Kan[/tag], and these tiles will be placed in the right corner, and you get to draw 1 tile and then discard 1 tile. This is called a Closed Kan and [tag]the Quad formed here is considered a kind of Triplet[/tag].","Let\'s call for this Closed Kan!","Shame that we didn\'t win with the drawn tile. Let\'s discard it.","That\'s what we were waiting for! Call [tag]Ron[/tag] on this tile!","In the upper left corner, there are 5 tiles, but only one is revealed. Isn\'t it strange?","This is the Dora indicator area, they will indicate the shining Dora tiles.\n[tag]The tile next in order after the revealed indicator tile is Dora[/tag]. If the 1 Man is revealed, then the 2 Man in your hand is Dora.","When you win, the more Dora tiles you have in your hand, the more points you win!","When you have neither All Simples nor Triplet of Prevalent/Seat Wind, what can you do? Since we haven\'t called Chii or Pon yet, we can call [tag]Riichi[/tag], it\'s also a very common Yaku.","Tap the Riichi button, [tag]pay 1000 points[/tag] as Riichi bet and discard a tile to make your hand Tenpai!","Which tile can you discard to achieve Tenpai?","No, not that one.\nYou need 4 Sequence/Triplets + 1 Pair to win.","Riichi, nyaa!","While paying 1000 points is a pain and [tag]you can\'t change your hand after calling Riichi[/tag], you will have Riichi as Yaku and you only need to draw a tile and discard it until you win!","I win! Ippatsu Tsumo!","[tag]Ippatsu[/tag] is a Yaku that comes into effect if the player wins within the next turn after declaring Riichi i.e. before their next discard (without interruptions from other players\' calls)!","As a reward for winning with Riichi, you also get the chance to have another Dora coming into effect! Let\'s check out what the Ura Dora tile is!","It\'s a pity we didn\'t have any Ura Dora tiles in this hand. But even like this, we win with bigger winning points since we have both Riichi and Ippatsu!","Oh, you are awake! I have played the game halfway for you, nyaa!\nCheck out your hand, we have so many Man tiles, nyaa!","Sorry, this hand looks a bit weird...","This hand is aiming for a Yaku called [tag]Half Flush[/tag], where aside from Honor tiles, all the number tiles belong to one suit. Currently, we are waiting for 1/4/7 Man, making this a very advantageous hand.","But as we have discarded the 1 Man before, that means we are in Tenpai waiting for tiles including one that was discarded before by ourselves. This status is called [tag]Discard Furiten[/tag].","When one is in Furiten,\nthey can only win by Tsumo (drawing the winning tiles by oneself),\nand not by Ron (calling on another player\'s discard)!","Aside from [tag]Discard Furiten[/tag], there are also two other types of Furiten called [tag]Temporary Furiten[/tag] and [tag]Riichi Furiten[/tag], but I won\'t go deep into these here, nyaa.","Grrr, we can\'t wait for the other three players to discard any of the winning tiles in this situation!\nTry to draw the winning tile on your own! Believe in yourself!","That\'s a win by [tag]Tsumo[/tag] for you! Good job!","=====Today\'s matches haven\'t started yet.=====","=====Today\'s matches have all ended.=====","=====The match has started!=====","=====The match has finished!=====","East {0}, Ichihime\'s hand is {1} tile(s) from Tenpai.","Turn {0}.","Ichihime pulls a useful tile, she\'s now {0} tile(s) from Tenpai.","Ichihime pulls a useful tile, she\'s got Tenpai!","{0} smiles and throws the Riichi bet. Riichi!","Ichihime chooses Hidden Tenpai.","Ichihime is in Tenpai with open calls.","{0} wins with Tsumo! {1} points!","{0} deals in! {1} wins with Ron! {2} points!","It\'s Yakuman: {0}!!","It\'s Double Yakuman: {0}!!!","Draw! Ichihime has Tenpai!","Draw! Ichihime is in No-ten...","{0} gets negative points, match is over!","In this round, Ichihime\'s ranking is: {0}!","It\'s Counted Yakuman!!","Ichihime stretches lazily.","Ichihime\'s expression gets serious","Ichihime\'s hand is shaking.","Ichihime hands over the point sticks reluctantly.","Ichihime has tears in her eyes and looks full of grievances.","Ichihime is in a rage and clenches her teeth.","Ichihime shows a smug smirk!","Ichihime hums a song of victory!","Ichihime put her hands on her hips and laughed excitedly!","Ichihime stops thinking and pushes every shiny button!","Ichihime has set her mind on All Simples and discards all terminal tiles!","Ichihime makes an interesting decision and chooses a badly-formed Tenpai hand!","Ichihime exudes a duelist-like aura, and the Riichi bet in her hand can\'t wait to be played!","With her wild instinct, Ichihime has kept all the tiles the other players are aiming for in her hand.","Ichihime\'s hand tiles are in pairs and look super orderly!","Ichihime has chosen a simple tactic, declaring Riichi as soon as she could, aiming for a quick win!","Ichihime looks at her hand tiles, how shiny they are!","Under the presence of Ichihime, a wave-like pattern appears on the table!","Flowers bloom behind Ichihime!","Ichihime looks at her tiles of the same suit and doesn\'t know which to discard. What a luxurious thing to worry about!","Ichihime has entered the Zone, she is getting a grasp of everything!","Ichihime\'s initial hand is so orderly, she has Tenpai at the start of the game!","Ichihime declares \"Kan, nyaa!\" The place where she placed the Quad shines brightly!","Ichihime feels her hand tiles shaking, this must be what being chosen by heaven feels like!","Ichihime hasn\'t had the chance to arrange her hand yet and a tile has already taken the shape of a dragon, rising to the sky, becoming one of the stars above!","Ichihime\'s hand looks random, but hides a mysterious glow underneath!","The mirror behind Ichihime shows many reflections of her, like the futures from parallel words.","Ichihime raises her head towards the night sky, and sees that the stars have already aligned for her victory!","East {0}, {1} Repeat, Ichihime\'s hand is {2} tile(s) from Tenpai.","South {0}, Ichihime\'s hand is {1} tile(s) from Tenpai.","South {0}, {1} Repeat, Ichihime\'s hand is {2} tile(s) from Tenpai.","Summer Limited Event - Hand of Meow has started! On the Train menu, consume Stamina to raise one of Ichihime\'s stats!","One Han City\'s Daily Tournament has 4 rounds each day. Send Ichihime to Battle, and complete all matches for that day to gain a ranking!","Check out Ichihime\'s match results on Match Log. There is also some mysterious content to unlock!","Complete daily event missions to gain extra Cat Food Cans to recharge Ichihime\'s stamina.\nMeet the requirements on Event Rewards to get limited rewards!","Chapter 1","Chapter 2","Chapter 3","Chapter 4","Revision","Mahjong Tiles","Yaku","Riichi","Furiten","Go over what we learned","Gongratulation on the win, nyaa!","Gongratulation on the win, nyaa!\nThis is the end of today\'s practice session! You can review the tutorial by chapter, or just check out the revision!","","","","","","","","","","請確認重啟後的語言版本所顯示的時間皆為UTC+8時區時間。\nPlease confirm that the time displays in-game will be in (UTC+8) after restarting.\n게임을 다시 시작한 후, 게임 내 시간이 (UTC+8)로 표시되는지 확인해 주세요.","Please confirm that the time displays in-game will be in (UTC-7) after restarting.\n請確認重啟後的語言版本所顯示的時間皆為UTC-7時區時間。\n게임을 다시 시작한 후, 게임 내 시간이 (UTC-7)로 표시되는지 확인해 주세요.","Agree to the","TERMS OF USE","PRIVACY POLICY","","","Account Deletion","","","게임을 다시 시작한 후, 게임 내 시간이 (GMT+9)로 표시되는지 확인해 주세요.\nPlease confirm that the time displays in-game will be in (GMT+9) after restarting.\n請確認重啟後的語言版本所顯示的時間皆為GMT+9時區時間。","Once the account is deleted, you can no longer use this game account (Other games under your Yostar Account will not be affected). All data of this account including game progress, earnings, and bindings with third-party accounts will be erased.\n\nI have carefully read the above information and confirm proceeding with account deletion.","Confirm","Cancel","Please type in DELETE and confirm deleting this account.","Confirm","The account deletion will be completed on {0}. There is a 30-day cooling-off period for account deletion. If you log in to the account again during this period, the account deletion will be canceled and your account will be restored.","The account deletion will be completed on {0}. If you log in to the account again before then, the account deletion will be canceled and your account will be restored.","Cancel","Login","Account deleted.","Account restored.","The account deletion will be completed on {0}. If you want to cancel the account deletion process, please log in once using the app version of the game (Android or iOS).","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","Please enter verification code.","","","","","Instructions","","","","","Dear Jyanshi Sama, to make sure we can keep providing you good service, please bind you account with an email address.","Account already bound to email.","PayPal","Stripe","MasterCard","Visa","Toss","PayPay","CreditCard","Au","Docomo","Softbank","WebMoney","認証に成功しました","リクエストIDが存在しません","認証コードの有効期限が過ぎています","認証に失敗しました","SMS認証が行われていません","生年月日を正しく入力してください","口座情報に誤りがあります","入力された氏名に使用できない文字が含まれています","口座情報が登録されていません","リクエスト回数が多すぎます","SMS送信に失敗しました","accessToken検証に失敗しました","解除に成功しました","解除のリクエストが見つかりません","SMSの認証に失敗しました","注文が見つかりません","注文に対する認証SMSが送信されていません","注文に対する認証SMSが存在しません","支払いに失敗しました","口座情報の読み込みに失敗しました","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","","Please state your reason for reporting [{0}]","Unfriendly behavior in match","Aggressive behavior towards other players in match","Nickname that violates rules","Inapproprioate nickname","Leaving match early or AFK","Intentionally prolonging the match","Cheating","Illegal use of third-party tools","Revealing hands","Intentional giving tiles/wins to another player","Game","Turn","Mandatory","Please provide detailed information (non-mandatory, up to 60 characters)","Report","Please provide information for the report","Reported Player","Report Type","Details","None","Choose Character","You can still change the character \nafter choosing","Please choose one path.","Next","Please choose your desired character first, nyaa.","Please choose an unowned character as the UP character.","Previous","Confirm","You have obtained all selectable regular characters.","You already have this character. Please choose another character that you do not have.","Please choose one path.\nYou already own all selectable regular characters in Sakura Path.","Please choose one path.\nYou already own all selectable regular characters in Bamboo Path.","Congratulations! You\'ve obtained your chosen character. The Fated Summon is now closed.","Mahjong Soul promises that all games are randomly generated. At the beginning of each match, the tile wall is already pre-determined, so the tiles issued in each game will not be changed, or influenced by any external factor. To support this statement, we have introduced a verification system. \n(The verification system used before May 23rd, 2023 is MD5, after the maintenance on May 23rd, 2023 it was upgraded to SHA-256 system, and after the update on February 27th, 2024 it has been further upgraded to SHA-256 system with salt value added.)\n\nEach tile has a unique code. \"Man\" tiles are represented by \"m\" (1m-9m), \"Pin\" tiles are represented by \"p\" (1p-9), \"Sou\" tiles are represented by \"s\" (1s-9s) and word tiles are represented by \"z\" (1z-7z, in the order of East, South, West, North, White, Green, and Red). For Red Fives: Red 5 Man is 0m, Red 5 Pin is 0p, Red 5 Sou is 0s. As such, each tile wall can be represented by a unique series of codes (tile wall code). \n\nFor SHA-256 verification (after February 27th, 2024, for security purposes a salt value has been added for the SHA-256 verification process)\n1. During the match, players can click the Dora Indicator on the top left corner to view and record the SHA-256 codes for both \"tile wall code + salt value\" and \"salt value\". The \"salt value\" is a random string of characters generated for each flush of tile wall.\n2. After a match, players can go to Log and verify the SHA-256 codes for \"tile wall code + salt value\" and \"salt value\" in each game (recorded in the Log) against the SHA-256 codes recorded when the game was played. The SHA-256 codes obtained during the game should be consistent with the SHA-256 codes in the Log, and this would prove that the tile wall was not changed during the game.\n\nFor MD5 verification (before May 23rd, 2023):\n1. During the match, players can click the Dora Indicator on the top left corner to view and record the tile wall MD5 code. Each flush of tile wall generates one set of MD5 code.\n2. After a match, players can go to Log and verify the MD5 code in each game (recorded in the Log) against the value recorded when the game was played. The MD5 code obtained during the game should be consistent with the MD5 code in the Log. \n3. Enter the tile wall code in an MD5 generator and it will show the corresponding MD5 code. You can compare the MD5 code generated with the MD5 code provided in game.","SHA-256 Code for \"Tile Wall Code + Salt Value\":","SHA-256 Code for \"Salt Value\":","Salt Value:","Manage Tournament","Manage","Create Tournament","This name cannot be used, please edit","Verification in process, you cannot edit the tournament name for the time being","The start time must be after the creation time and no more than 365 days later.","The end time must be after the start time and no more than 365 days later.","I hereby promise that the tournament won\'t be used for gambling or other illegal activities.","Confirm Creation","Use 60 Jade to create tournament?","On Mahjong Soul Tournament Management website, you can manage more aspects of your tournament. Go now?","Please review tournament info","You need to tick the commitment clause","Tournament Name","Start time","End time","Deadline","Tournament Type","Official Tournament","Hot Tournament","Normal Tournament","Open Display","Match Mode","Riichi Mahjong","Rounds","4 Matches","8 Matches","10+20s","20+0s","More Options","25 characters or less","On","Off","JAN","FEB","MAR","APR","MAY","JUN","JUL","AUG","SEP","OCT","NOV","DEC","Mon","Tue","Wed","Thu","Fri","Sat","Sun","","","Registered","Registration successful","Insufficient Jade","Go","Create","Register","Being verified","Registration not open","Registered, please wait for the tournament admin to approave","Connecting chat server...","Connected","Failed to connect","Auto matching","Sort by","Total end score of last 3 matches","Total end score of last 5 matches","Highest total end score of 2 consecutive matches","Highest total end score of 3 consecutive matches","Highest total end score of 4 consecutive matches","Highest total end score of 5 consecutive matches","None","Load Preset Rules","Default Rules","RMU Rules","M.League Rules","Mahjong Saikyosen Rules","Saikouisen Rules","Nihon Pro Mahjong Rules","Mahjong Union Rules","Emote","4-Player","3-Player","Ranking Restrictions","Novice I","Novice II","Novice III","Adept I","Adept II","Adept III","Expert I","Expert II","Expert III","Master I","Master II","Master III","Saint I","Saint II","Saint III","Celestial","How many matches each player can play","Default Starting Points","Minimum Points to Win","Tournament Information","Rules","Rank and Match Length Restriction","Upper Limit","Riichi Bet Points","Repeat Counter Points","Noten Penalty: 1 Tenpai Player","Noten Penalty: 2 Tenpai Players","Noten Penalty: 3 Tenpai Players","Uma - 2nd","Uma - 3rd","Uma - 4th","Red Five","No Red Five","2 Red Five","3 Red Five","4 Red Five","Commonly Used Rules","Han Limit","Kiriage Mangan","Head-Bump","Others","Hand of Man","Off","Pay Responsibility","Big Three Dragons & Four Big Winds","Big Three Dragons & Four Big Winds & Four Quads","Swap Calling","Last Turn Riichi","Double Wind 4 Fu","Dora","Dealer Repeats","In-Match Draws","Yakuman","Ura Dora","Kan Dora","Reveal Dora immediately after calling Open Kan","Kan-Ura Dora","Dealer Repeats on Win","Four-Kan Abortive Draw","Triple-Ron Draw","Robbing a Kan for Thirteen Orphans","Multiple Yakuman","Ranking","Match Arrangement","Nickname","Match Count","Random Seats","Add Computer","Arrange","East","South","West","North","Ready Players","Start","Points","Empty","Arranged","AI(Normal)","AI(Easy)","AI(Draw&Discard)","No Rank","No Player","Tournament ID: {0}","This tournament has no ranking setting","Tounament Created","Tournament Info","Assigned match is about to start, please wait","Assigned match started","ID:{0}","Current tournament has no ongoing season. Please check the tournament management page.","Server connection error. If you cannot enter the game, please restart the game.","Open x10","Tools","Start Game","Continue Game","End this round of game, and you can start a new game","Special Event - Sky-High Ambition has begun! Accumulate PT from winning hands to reach the target PT and clear each level. Strive to conquer all levels!","Upgrades and talismans in the shop can provide significant help on your path of challenges! Receiving the same talisman will upgrade it to an enhanced version!","Complete missions during the event to receive Event Illustration, Summon Scroll, Limited Title, and Limited Animated Tablecloth as rewards!","The enhancement points you gain can make you even stronger, soaring straight to the sky! (Enhanced abilities take effect at the start of a new game round)","Special Event: Sky-High Ambition\nEvent Period: 8/19 - 9/12 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nAim higher, faster, and stronger! Uphold the belief in mahjong and soar straight into the clouds! \nComplete missions during the event to receive Summon Scroll, Limited Title, and Limited Animated Tablecloth as rewards!\n\nGame Process\n- The target of each game round is to clear the levels. There are two phases, Level Phase and Shop Phase.\n- In the Level Phase, you will face 15 levels, with every 3rd level being a boss level that has additional restrictions.\n- You need to assemble winning hands in the Level Phase to score PT; only by reaching the target PT can you clear the level.\n- After clearing a level, you enter the Shop Phase where you can use Star Coins earned during the Level Phase to purchase items or enhance abilities.\n- Clearing all 15 levels results in a victory for that game round.\n- Upon victory, you can choose to challenge more levels.\n\nLevel Phase\n- The game uses 108 tiles, removing 2-8 Man tiles.\n- At the beginning of each level, you receive 13 hand tiles, 36 tiles in the Tile Wall, and 1 Dora indicator, including 6 open tiles in the Tile Wall.\n\n- Before drawing any tiles, you can exchange hand tiles:\n-- Any number of hand tiles can be exchanged with the Tile Pool but not with the Tile Wall.\n-- Each exchange consumes 1 tile exchange count. You start with 2 at the beginning of the game round.\n\n-- After you finish with the tile exchange, the drawing starts\n-- You draw tiles in order from the Tile Wall. Drawing tiles and winning follow the standard mahjong rules.\n-- When your hand meets winning conditions, you can declare a win and calculate the winning PT.\n-- Unlike standard mahjong, after winning, you can continue adjusting your hand for an optimal state.\n-- There is no Riichi rule in this mode.\n\n- PT calculation\n-- Winning PT = Total PT of all hand tiles x Han count\n-- PT per Tile: Number tiles = 5 PT, Honor tiles = 10 PT\n-- Han is calculated based on standard mahjong\'s Yaku.\n-- Talimans can influence PT and Han.\n\n- Level Completion\n-- Meeting the target PT for each level means you have cleared the level and you enter the Continuous Draw Mode.\n-- In Continuous Draw Mode, the remaining tiles in the Tile Wall are opened directly.\n-- If tiles in the Tile Wall meet winning conditions, PT is settled immediately. The level ends when all tiles in the Tile Wall are drawn.\n-- Star Coin rewards are given based on the current level\'s difficulty.\n-- Extra Star Coins are awarded for reaching 2x, 3x, or 5x the target PT.\n\n- Failure Conditions\n-- The game round ends if you cannot achieve the target PT by the final draw tile.\n\nShop Phase\n- In the Shop Phase, you spend Star Coins to upgrade abilities or purchase talisman packs.\n- Ability Upgrades: Increase the number of tile exchanges, open tiles, and Dora Indicators for the current game round.\n- Talisman Pack Purchases: Choose talisman packs of different rarity. Open the pack to select one preferred talisman from three options or skip.\n- Duplicate talismans can upgrade existing ones to strengthened versions with enhanced effects.\n- Talismans have a possession limit.\n\nInitial Enhancements\n- Completing event missions grants enhancement points.\n- Use these points in the main event page under \"Enhancement\" for initial enhancements.\n- Initial Enhancements include: Starting Star Coins, number of talisman packs in the shop, quality of talisman packs in the shop, shop refresh price, and talisman limit.\n- Initial Enhancements can be reset anytime, returning all enhancement points.\n- Initial Enhancements take effect in the next new game round after being applied.","Choose a talisman","Choose","Cost","Target PT","Level Reward","Tile Pool","{0} Tile(s) Left","Dora","Talisman {0}/{1}","{0}Target","Please choose any number of tiles and exchange them","Han","PT","Target PT","{0}% PT Reward","Refresh","Next Level","Tile Exchanges","Dora Indicator","Open Tiles","Price","Open","Level Failed","Acquired Talisman","Wins","Biggest Win","Continue Challenge","","Event Rewards","All","Incomplete","Completed","Claim All","Enhancement","Reset","Enhanced!","Do you want to reset enhancements? After the reset, all enhanced abilities are set to Lv0, and all enhancement points are returned.","Enhanced abilities take effect at the start of a new game round","Collection","Talisman","Best Record","Event Record","Highest Cleared Level:","Upgrade","Level List","Total","No Data","Upgrade Owned Talisman","Sell","Empty","Owned","Enhancement Point","Sky-High Ambition event item. Can be used to enhance abilities. Will be fully returned when you reset the enhancements.","Star Coins at the start","Number of Talisman packs","Quality of Talisman packs","Shop refresh cost","Talisman limit","At the start of a new game, Star Coins held: {0}","Number of talisman packs in the shop: {0}","Talisman packs of higher rarity are more likely to appear in the shop. Current level: {0}","The cost for the first refresh of talisman packs, Star Coin: {0}","The maximum number of talismans you can own at the same time: {0}",">>{0}","Original effect","You have reached the talisman limit, please sell 1 talisman before you choose this talisman.","Spend {0} Star Coin(s) and refresh all talisman packs in the shop?","Level Restriction","Unlocks after clearing Level {0}","Server Ranking","Friend Ranking","Player Nickname","Highest Level","High Score","Last updated: {0}","Event in maintenance now, please check out later.","Do you wish to leave this room?","Collab Limited Decoration Pack","K","Auto Kita","Gifting this gift will make your bond reach max limit. Continue?","Show Pro/CC Mark","Collection number: {0}","Ranked Match","Event","Logs prior on or before 2024/08/20 can only be filtered by date.","Points Calculation","Non-Dealer\'s Points Chart","Dealer\'s Points Chart","Fu Calculation Chart","Middle Tiles: All the 2-8 tiles of Man/Pin/Sou","Terminal Tiles: All the 1 and 9 tiles of Man/Pin/Sou, Wind Tiles, and Dragon Tiles","Open Triplet: A triplet completed by Pon. When achieving Ron, a triplet formed with a Pair in your hand is also considered an Open Triplet","Concealed Triplet: A triplet completed without making a call","Open Quad: Make a call for Open Kan or Added Kan","Concealed Quad: Call Kan for 4 identical tiles in your own hand","Double Wind: The pair is both the Seat Wind and the Prevalent Wind.","Single-wait Tenpai: The hand completes 4 Mentsu, waiting for a single tile to complete a pair to win.","Closed-wait Tenpai: The hand completes 3 Mentsu, 1 Pair, and a combination like 24, waiting for a 3 to win.","Edge-wait Tenpai: The hand completes 3 Mentsu, 1 Pair, and a combination like 12 or 89, waiting for a 3 or 7 to win.","","Continue","Start","Please enter your answer within {0} characters","Filters","Date","From","To","Today","Last 7d","Last 30d","Rank","1st","2nd","3rd","4th","{0}","High Score","Baiman or above","Sanbaiman or above","Yakuman or above","Mode","4-Player","3-Player","Bronze Room","Silver Room","Gold Room","Jade Room","Throne Room","Search","Collection:","Ranked Match","All","One More Match","How about another match of","","Matchmaking","Cancel","Fortune Charm Effect: {0}d","Expires Soon","{0}h","{0}m","Emote Preview","The server will enter maintenance in [tag]{0}[/tag]","Player","Rank/PT Change","Points","Riichi","Ron","Tsumo","Dora","Ura Dora","Submit","The Log feature is under maintenance, please try again later.","Limitless Asura","Special Rules: Limitless Asura\n- Before the tile distribution, all players will have a replacement tile in their hand.\n- The replacement tile cannot be discarded, used for Chii/Pon/Kan, or exchanged with other players.\n- The replacement tile can be considered any tile except a red Dora (including as the 5th tile of a kind)\n- When the replacement tile is counted as a Dora, it follows the usual Han Bonus calculation.\n- When winning, the replacement tile will be calculated in a way that maximizes the hand\'s value (excluding Ura Dora).\n- After the Hand distribution, select 3 tiles and exchange them with other players.\n- The ending condition of each match has been changed from 1 winner to 3 winners.\n- Upon winning, the points will be calculated in real-time, and the tiles in hand will remain hidden. The match will end when a player is busted.\n- When a match ends, and there are less than 3 winners, it is regarded as a Draw.\n- There will be no Repeat Counter, regardless of whether the dealer has achieved Tenpai, the next match starts from 0 Repeat Counter.\n- When Draw happens during the match, regardless of whether there are winners, the match will restart from 0 Repeat Counter.\n- In the same match, players who have already won will not be participating in the Draw settlement.\n- When Draw happens, players who have not achieved Tenpai will pay 1000 points to each Tenpai player.\n- Players can choose to win when achieving Robbing a Kan (including Thirteen Orphans Concealed Quad). When a player wins by achieving Robbing a Kan, the Kan holds.\n- When Four-Kan Abortion happens after Robbing a Kan, Robbing a Kan holds, and the match will restart due to the Draw during the match.\n- Deal-in while in Riichi.\n- If the points left are above 1000 after paying for deal-in, the Riichi holds.\n- If the points left are below 1000 after paying for deal-in, the Riichi fails, and the match continues.\n- If the points left are below 0 after paying for deal-in, the match ends.\n- Player doesn\'t have to pay responsibility for causing other players\' Big Three Dragons or Four Big Winds.","Tournament","Collection","","Chaotic Wall Break","Change Character","Random Character Settings","Random List","Specific: A specified character/outfit will be used for the match.","When a Ranked Match or Tournament Match starts, a random chracter/outfit from the above selected options will be chosen for the match.\nWhen you enter a Friendly Match room, a random chracter/outfit from the above selected options will be chosen for the match.","Random: A random chracter/outfit from the selected options will be chosen for the match.","The random character/outfit feature is not yet available.","Confirm to clear the list?","This character is on your Random List. Confirm to remove and hide this character?","Game feature in maintenance now, please check out later.","Mission updated, please check out the details once more.","AI Avatar","Comes into effect when you add AI individually in Friendly Match","Random owned character","Ichihime\'s default outfit","Pass & Discard","","","","","","","","","","","","","Selected Win","Log Link","Submit","Choose winning game","Highlight","Recent {0} Matches","Completed {0} time(s)","No deal-ins in the whole match, and achieving winning hands with Mangan or higher for 4 times.","Placing 1st consecutively for 5 times. (First-place wins in 3-Player and 4-Player are counted separately)","Ending a match with winning a hand with Baiman or higher, and jumping from last place to 1st.","Winning with Yakuman.","Ending a match with more than 100,000 points.","No deal-ins in the whole match, and achieving winning hands with Mangan or higher for 4 times. (For East Only or Two-Wind Matches, no AI)","Placing 1st consecutively for 5 times. (For East Only or Two-Wind Matches, no AI. First-place wins in 3-Player and 4-Player are counted separately)","Ending a match with winning a hand with Baiman or higher, and jumping from last place to 1st. (For East Only or Two-Wind Matches, no AI)","Winning with Yakuman. (For East Only or Two-Wind Matches, no AI)","Ending a match with more than 100,000 points. (For East Only or Two-Wind Matches, no AI)","Placing 1st consecutively for 5 times. (First-place wins in 3-Player and 4-Player are counted separately)","Ending a match with 2 or more opponents reaching negative points.","Winning Statistics","Ranking Statistics","Open Call","Hidden Tenpai","Based on the 100 most recent matches","Recent High Score","Choose from Log({0}-{1})","No winning record found in this log.","Please submit the log link.","Select Character","Select Emote","View this log?","Analyze","Analyzed","Analyzing","Start Analysis","Enter","Return","Analysis Attempt(s)","Single analysis results are retained for 7 days.","Use MAKA to analyze your logs from Ranked matches, as well as Friendly and Tournament matches that use the same rules as Ranked matches. It will provide scores and playing suggestions.\n\nDaily analysis limit: 10 attempts (30 attempts daily with Fortune Charm in effect). Resets every day at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7).\n\nSingle analysis results are retained for 7 days, so please check them promptly.\n\nAfter analysis, MAKA offers suggestions based on the game situation for your reference.\nA higher number on a tile or button indicates a stronger recommendation for that choice.\n\nIn the Round List, you can view scores for each round.\nIn the Turn List, you can see where your decisions differ from MAKA\'s suggestions.\nAdditionally, use the \"Prev/Next Diff\" buttons to quickly locate these differences.\n\nWe hope MAKA helps you review and enhance your mahjong skills.","Insufficient remaining attempts.","Currently analyzing other logs, please wait.","Analysis results expired, please reanalyze this log.","Not Analyzed","Off","On","Complete","Overall Score:","Match Score:","Prev Diff","Next Diff","Perfect Match(Ranked Match)","Unbroken Wins(Ranked Match)","Stunning Upset(Ranked Match)","Yakuman Mastery(Ranked Match)","Top Scorer(Ranked Match)","Perfect Match(Friendly Match)","Unbroken Wins(Friendly Match)","Stunning Upset(Friendly Match)","Yakuman Mastery(Friendly Match)","Friendship Ender(Friendly Match)","Perfect Match(Event Match)","Unbroken Wins(Event Match)","Stunning Upset(Event Match)","Yakuman Mastery(Event Match)","Power Smash(Event Match)","Bonus Rewards","Level Rewards","Talisman Challenge","Challenges Cleared","Talisman Collected","Suit","Man","Sou","Pin","Honor","Added Soul Tile","Initial Tile Exchanges","Initial tile exchanges at the new start: {0}","Shop Phase","The brand-new Sky-High Ambition: Firework Glee event has begun! This game mode uses 108 tiles, removing 2-8 Man tiles. Accumulate PT from winning hands to reach the target PT and clear each level. Strive to conquer all levels!","Upgrades and talismans in the shop can provide significant help on your path toward challenges! Receiving the same talisman will upgrade it to an enhanced version!","During the event, complete missions to receive Sage\'s Bag, Event Illustration, and more!","The enhancement points you gain can make you even stronger, soaring straight to the sky! (Enhanced abilities will take effect at the start of a new game)","Special Event - Sky-High Ambition: Firework Glee\nEvent Period: 1/20 - 5/25 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nAim higher, faster, and stronger! Embrace the Mahjong spirit and soar to the azure skies!\nSky-High Ambition is back with thrilling new talismans waiting for you!\nDuring the event, complete missions to receive Sage\'s Bag, Event Illustration, and more.\n\nGame Process\n- The target of each game is to clear the levels. There are two phases, Level Phase and Shop Phase.\n- In the Level Phase, you will face 15 levels, with every 3rd level being a boss level that has additional restrictions.\n- You need to assemble winning hands in the Level Phase to score PT; only by reaching the target PT can you clear the level.\n- After clearing a level, you enter the Shop Phase where you can use Star Coins earned during the Level Phase to purchase items or enhance abilities.\n- Clearing all 15 levels results in a victory for that game round.\n- Upon victory, you can choose to challenge more levels.\n\nLevel Phase\n- The game uses 108 tiles, removing 2-8 Man tiles.\n- At the start of each level, you receive 13 hand tiles, 36 tiles in the Tile Wall, and 1 Dora indicator, with 6 opened tiles in the Tile Wall.\n\n- Before drawing any tiles, you can exchange hand tiles:\n-- Any number of hand tiles can be exchanged with the Tile Pool but not with the Tile Wall.\n-- Each exchange consumes 1 tile exchange count. You start with 3 at the beginning of the game round.\n\n- After you finish with the tile exchange, the drawing starts:\n-- You draw tiles in order from the Tile Wall. Drawing tiles and winning follow the standard mahjong rules.\n-- When your hand meets winning conditions, you can declare a win and calculate the winning PT.\n-- Unlike standard mahjong, after winning, you can continue adjusting your hand for an optimal state.\n-- There is no Riichi rule in this mode.\n\n- PT Calculation\n-- Winning PT = Total PT of all hand tiles x Han count\n-- PT per Tile: Number tiles = 5 PT, Honor tiles = 10 PT\n-- Han is calculated based on standard mahjong\'s Yaku.\n-- Talimans can influence PT and Han.\n\n- Level Completion\n-- Meeting the target PT for each level means you have cleared the level and you enter the Continuous Draw Mode.\n-- In Continuous Draw Mode, the remaining tiles in the Tile Wall are opened directly.\n-- If tiles in the Tile Wall meet winning conditions, PT is settled immediately. The level ends when all tiles in the Tile Wall are drawn.\n-- Star Coin rewards are given based on the current level\'s difficulty.\n-- Extra Star Coins are awarded for reaching 2x, 3x, or 5x of the target PT.\n\n- Failure Condition\n-- The game round ends if you cannot achieve the target PT by the final drawn tile.\n\nShop Phase\n- In the Shop Phase, you can sell your talismans or spend Star Coins to upgrade abilities and purchase talisman packs.\n- Ability Upgrades: Increase the number of opened tiles, Dora indicators, and added Soul tiles for the current game round.\n- Talisman Pack Purchases: Choose talisman packs of different rarity. Open the pack to select one preferred talisman from three options or skip.\n- Duplicate talismans can upgrade existing ones to enhanced versions with stronger effects.\n- Talismans have a possession limit.\n\nInitial Enhancements\n- Completing event missions grants enhancement points.\n- Use these points in the main event page under \"Enhancement\" for initial enhancements.\n- Initial Enhancements include: initial Star Coins, the number of talisman packs in the shop, the rarity of talismans in the shop, shop refresh price, talisman limit, and initial tile exchanges.\n- Initial Enhancements can be reset anytime, returning all enhancement points.\n- Initial Enhancements take effect in the next new game round after being applied.","1/20 - 5/25 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","Locked tiles cannot be drawn; each grants +{0} Han when winning.","Special Rules: Chaotic Wall Break Instructions\r\n\r\n3 Dora indicators will be revealed at the beginning of the match. 5 Dora indicators can be revealed at most.\r\n\r\nOne player will receive the Wareme mark at the beginning of the match, and once this player has discarded 5 tiles in total, the Wareme mark will move to a random player (including the original holder).\r\n\r\nThe score of the marked player will be doubled after winning or losing (not including Riichi Bets and Round Bets).","Search Character","Enter character or CV name; supports fuzzy search in EN/CN/JP/KR.","Regular","Exclusive","Sakura","Bamboo","Search","Change Theme Name","Decoration Theme {0}","[Weekly Rotation Mode]","Refreshes in:","Go to Shop","Choose Outfit","No characters match.","Outfit not yet acquired.","Character Sort - Marked","Character Sort - Unmarked","Characters moved here will be automatically marked.","Press and hold, then drag the avatar to change display order or star mark status.","Save","Characters moved here will automatically get their marks removed.","Changes not saved. Do you want to exit?","Luck","Skill","Insight","Intuition","Wisdom","Start Match","Matchmaking","Not enough Boost Cans left; complete weekly missions to earn more","Winner\'s Path","The Sparrow Cup kicks off, and Ichihime is ready to take the stage!","Restart","Upgrade","Rankings","Riichi Siege","High stakes, big rewards – it is all or nothing in this battle! Dive into the new 4-Player East special mode, Riichi Siege!","Collab Limited Event - Sparrow Cup\nEvent Period: 4/22 - 5/13 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nThe Winner\'s Path event in the Sparrow Cup has begun! Ichihime\'s training journey is full of surprises. Join her in aiming for the highest score! Help Ichihime enhance her Attributes to compete against other competitors and reach the top in the competition.\n\nAbout Winner\'s Path\n- The Winner\'s Path consists of 10 rounds, each with 4 training phases and 1 match phase.\n- Each round starts with 4 training phases, followed by a match phase.\n- In each training phase, choose a way to enhance Ichihime\'s Attributes. Outcomes can be Great Success, Success, or Failure, each resulting in different stat changes.\n- During match phases, Ichihime competes with 3 random opponents in mahjong, and the results are recorded.\n- Training is not available during match phases.\n- Matches follow 4-Player East rules; order bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +5, 3rd -5, 4th -15.\n- After 10 rounds, all the match results will be added to the rankings.\n\nAbout Incidents\nIchihime will face various incidents during training and match phases.\n- Different choices during incidents lead to varied outcomes.\n- The outcomes are affected by Ichihime\'s Attributes.\n- Incidents may grant Ichihime new Talents, Attribute boosts, or affect Ichihime\'s match performance.\n- Certain Talents may unlock special options ensuring Great Success.\n\nAbout Ichihime\'s Attributes\n- [Luck] affects her starting hand and the quality of her draws.\n- [Skill] affects how quickly she can reach Tenpai.\n- [Insight] affects how likely she is to deal into other hands, as well as her awareness of others\' Tenpai.\n- [Intuition] affects her feel for the game and her chances of making Open Calls, Riichi, and Tsumo.\n- [Wisdom] affects the value of her winning hands.","The Winner\'s Path event has begun! Ichihime\'s training journey is full of surprises. Join her in aiming for the highest score!","High stakes, big rewards – it is all or nothing in this battle! Enjoy the brand-new special mode, Riichi Siege!","During the event, complete missions to claim various rewards including limited Illustration, limited Background, and Summon Scrolls! Plus, get Boost Cans to assist Ichihime\'s training.","You can review the collab event story at [Story].","Ranking","Player","Highest Score","999+","No Records","Increase Ichihime\'s initial Luck in a new game round.","Increase Ichihime\'s initial Skill in a new game round.","Increase Ichihime\'s initial Insight in a new game round.","Increase Ichihime\'s initial Intuition in a new game round.","Increase Ichihime\'s initial Wisdom in a new game round.","Reset","Currently +{0}","Remaining Upgrade Attempt(s)","Upgraded Attributes will take effect at the start of a new game round.","Current Score","Highest Score","Way of Luck","Way of Skill","Way of Insight","Way of Intuition","Way of Wisdom","Train","Training Phase","Start Match","Historical Record","Top Rankings","Sparrow Cup Round {0} begins!","Talent","Tile(s) from Tenpai","Tenpai","Log","Remaining Tile(s)","Sparrow Cup Round {0} ends.","Confirm","Score Ranking","Total Score","Attributes","Talents","Winning Rate:","Deal-In Rate:","Biggest Win:","Winning Streak:","Match Stats","End","Hold this area to hide popup content","Release to show popup content","Acquire Talent [{0}]!","{0}% Chance","Your {0} increased by {1}!","Your {0} decreased by {1}","Affected by Attribute {0}","Affected by Attributes {0} & {1}","Training Complete","Remaining Phase(s)","Results","Sparrow Cup","Ultimate Goal","Round {0}","Myself","Upgrade Successful!","Confirm Reset? All used upgrade points will be returned.","Acquire Talent [{0}]","Thinking","Best Record","Luck affects Ichihime\'s starting hand and the quality of her draws.","Skill affects how quickly Ichihime can reach Tenpai.","Insight affects how likely Ichihime is to deal into other hands, as well as her awareness of others\' Tenpai.","Intuition affects Ichihime\'s feel for the game and her chances of making Open Calls, Riichi, and Tsumo.","Wisdom affects the value of Ichihime\'s winning hands.","4/22 - 5/13 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","Special Rules: Riichi Siege\n\nWhen a player can declare Riichi, they can choose to pay extra points to enhance the Riichi effect.\n- Riichi: pay 1,000 points for 1 Han\n- True Riichi: pay 5,000 points for an extra +2 Han\n- Extreme Riichi: pay 10,000 points for an extra +4 Han\n- Double Riichi can also be enhanced, starting with a base of 2 Han.\n- Enhancing Riichi causes a glowing indicator to appear on the table, and the Han bonus is shown next to the player\'s avatar.\n- If you deal into multiple players\' winning hands, the points put on the table go to the winning player closest to you in turn order.\n- At the end of the game, all points put on the table go to the player in first place.\n\nMatch Mode: Riichi Siege - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nEntry Limit: 5,000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1,000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1,000 Coppers\nMatches played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60\nBond Point Bonus: 40\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if you finish in negativity.","Main Page","View","Match End","Speed","Skip Training","Match Review","Add Note","Current Note:","No note (up to 14 characters)","Invalid","*Please protect your personal information when livestreaming or posting game footage publicly.","Special Rules: Riichi Siege\n\nWhen a player can declare Riichi, they can choose to pay extra points to enhance the Riichi effect.\n- Riichi: pay 1,000 points for 1 Han\n- True Riichi: pay 5,000 points for an extra +2 Han\n- Extreme Riichi: pay 10,000 points for an extra +4 Han\n- Double Riichi can also be enhanced, starting with a base of 2 Han.\n- Enhancing Riichi causes a glowing indicator to appear on the table, and the Han bonus is shown next to the player\'s avatar.\n- If you deal into multiple players\' winning hands, the points put on the table go to the winning player closest to you in turn order.\n- At the end of the game, all points put on the table go to the player in first place.","Talents Acquired","Ichihime\'s {0} increased by {1}!","Triggered with Talent [{0}]","Open Call: {0}","Sparrow Cup","Train!","Compete!","Incidents and Talents","Order Bonus of 2nd place cannot be greater than that of the 1st place","Order Bonus of 3rd place cannot be greater than that of the 2nd place","Order Bonus of 4th place cannot be greater than that of the 3rd place","Summer Limited Event - Seaside Cafe\nEvent Period: 6/24 - 7/15 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\n\"Bringing the culinary stories of One Han City to the world?\"\nAnd so, Chef Red Panda set sail across the seas to open a brand-new Seaside Cafe!\nYuzu and Chef Red Panda invite you to join their team –\nComplete orders and win over every customer with delicious dishes!\n\nDuring the event, complete customer orders to earn Praise PT and claim rewards including the new limited Tile Back, Event Illustration, Summon Scroll, and more!\n\nAbout Orders\n- Every day at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7), a certain number of customers will arrive at Seaside Cafe with their orders.\n- Successfully complete orders to earn Praise PT and claim various rewards!\n- Some customer orders need two dishes. Completing these will reward you with even more Praise PT!\n\nAbout Food\n- During the event, complete daily missions to earn Red Panda Coins.\n- You can also get Red Panda Coins when winning in matches with no AI:\nWinning (Score below Mangan) +30\nWinning (Mangan) +60\nWinning (Haneman) +90\nWinning (Baiman) +120\nWinning (Sanbaiman) +180\nWinning (Yakuman and above) +240\n- Tap the food tray on the right to spend Red Panda Coins and get a new dish on the table.\n- Each food tray will give you only one of the two dishes shown.\n\nHow to Merge\n- Dishes on the table can be merged or used to complete orders.\n- Drag two identical dishes together to merge them into a higher-level dish of the same category.\n- Dishes of the highest level cannot be merged further.\n- Tap Recipes to view the merging paths.\n\nAbout Tips\n- Every time you merge items, there is a chance Tips will appear.\n- Drag Tips to the Collect pot and you will get Praise PT directly!\n- You can also merge Tips to create higher-level ones and earn even more Praise PT.\n- Only up to 10 Tips can appear each day.\n\nAbout Collecting\n- Drag any unwanted dishes to the Collect pot to receive Red Panda Coins in return.\n- Collecting dishes involves some loss of their value, so tread carefully!\n- If there is no other action taken in between, you can undo your last Collect action (except Tips).\n\nYuzu\'s Note\n- Always check what the customers want before picking a food tray!\n- Avoiding food waste is a lesson every friend of justice must learn!\n- Thanks to a magic spell, the dishes won\'t spoil.","or","Unlocks at {0} Praise PT","Daily missions will be refreshed at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7) every day.","You can also get Red Panda Coins by playing matches with no AI (the number depends on your winning points).","The table is full! Please clear some space first.","You don\'t have enough Red Panda Coins. Complete daily missions or play matches with no AI to earn more coins.","Click Effects","Linked to Lobby","Default","Mute when in background","Rank By","Total end score of last N matches","Highest total end score of N consecutive matches","Matches for Ranking","Can be set from 2 to 10.","Total end score of last {0} matches:","Highest total end score of {0} consecutive matches:","Last {0} matches Ranks:","Best continuous {0} games points:","Best continuous {0} games ranks:","Total end score of last {0} matches","Highest total end score of {0} consecutive matches","Last {0} matches Ranks","For assistance, please email our Customer Support team at: mjs.cs@yo-star.com","For further management, please visit the Tournament Management page on our official website: https://mahjongsoul.yo-star.com","The server is busy at the moment, please try again later.","Too many operations. Please try again later.","Seal","Recent Log","Set as Default","Cancel","Log {0}","Completion Time: {0}","Highest Level Score:","Highest Han:","Highest Winning PT:","Full Clears:","Levels Cleared:","Talismans Collected:","Seals Collected:","Most Packs Opened:","Most Star Coins Spent:","Star Coins Spent:","Packs Opened:","Clear {0} to unlock the ability to set a default talisman","Replace existing Seal","Normal","Rare","Legendary","Mythical","Obtain extra talisman","When the level starts, it shapeshifts!","The brand-new Sky-High Ambition: The Nyavengers event has begun! This game mode uses a 108-tile set, with the 2-8 Man tiles removed. Accumulate PT from winning hands to reach the target score and clear each level. Strive to conquer them all!","Upgrades and talismans from the shop offer a major advantage. Getting a duplicate talisman will upgrade it to a Plus version, and you may occasionally find special sealed talismans as well.","Complete missions to earn Sage\'s Bags, enhancement points, and more!","With the enhancement points you\'ve obtained, you can ascend to a new level of power! (All enhancements will activate at the start of your next game.)","Special Event - Sky-High Ambition: The Nyavengers\nEvent Period: Available for a long time\n\nThe goal is higher, faster, stronger! Embrace the spirit of mahjong and soar to new heights!\nSky-High Ambition is back again! Join the Nyavengers on a thrilling adventure – gather new companions, slay the fearsome dragon, and conquer the summit.\n\nGame Process\n- The goal of the game is to clear the levels. There are two phases, the Level Phase and the Shop Phase.\n- In the Level Phase, you will face 15 levels, with every 3rd level being a boss level that has additional restrictions.\n- You need to assemble winning hands in the Level Phase to score PT; only by reaching the target PT can you clear the level.\n- After clearing a level, you enter the Shop Phase, where you can use Star Coins earned during the Level Phase to purchase items or upgrade abilities.\n- Achieving a full clear of all 15 levels is considered a victory.\n- Upon completing a full clear, you can choose to challenge Ex levels.\n\nLevel Phase\n- The game uses a 108-tile set, with the 2-8 Man tiles removed.\n- At the start of each level, you receive 13 hand tiles. There are 36 tiles in the Tile Wall and 1 Dora indicator, with 6 tiles opened in the Tile Wall.\n\n- Before drawing, you can exchange hand tiles:\n-- Hand tiles can be exchanged with the Tile Pool but not with the Tile Wall.\n-- Each exchange consumes 1 tile exchange count. You start with 3 at the beginning of the game round.\n\n- After you finish with tile exchanges, the drawing starts:\n-- You draw tiles in order from the Tile Wall. Drawing tiles and winning follow the standard mahjong rules.\n-- When your hand meets winning conditions, you can declare a win and calculate the winning PT.\n-- Unlike standard mahjong, after winning, you can continue adjusting your hand for an optimal state.\n-- There is no Riichi rule in this mode.\n\n- PT Calculation\n-- Winning PT = Total PT of all hand tiles x Han count\n-- The total PT of your hand tiles is calculated based on the basic PT of each tile (see the Tile Pool for details).\n-- Han is calculated based on standard mahjong\'s Yaku.\n-- Talismans can influence PT and Han.\n-- Talismans are resolved in order from left to right.\n\n- Level Completion\n-- Meeting the target PT for each level means you have cleared the level, and you enter the Continuous Draw Mode.\n-- In the Continuous Draw Mode, the remaining tiles in the Tile Wall are opened directly.\n-- If tiles in the Tile Wall meet winning conditions, the winning PT will be calculated immediately. The level ends when all tiles in the Tile Wall are drawn.\n-- Level clear rewards (Star Coins & talisman packs) are given based on the current level\'s difficulty.\n-- Extra Star Coins are awarded for reaching 2x, 3x, or 5x of the target PT.\n-- Talismans that trigger at the end of the level will take effect upon level completion.\n\n- About Failure\n-- The game ends if you haven\'t reached the target PT when the last tile is drawn.\n\nShop Phase\n- In the Shop Phase, you can sell your talismans or spend Star Coins to upgrade abilities and purchase talisman packs.\n- Ability Upgrade: Increase the number of opened tiles, Dora indicators, and added Soul tiles for the current game round.\n- Talisman Pack Purchase: There are talisman packs of different rarities. Open a pack to choose one of the three talismans presented, or skip.\n- Duplicate talismans can upgrade existing ones to Plus versions with stronger effects.\n- When acquiring a talisman, it has a chance to come with a random-tier Seal.\n-- If you obtain a duplicate talisman that has a Seal, its Seal will replace your old one.\n- Talismans have a possession limit.\n\nInitial Enhancements\n- Completing event missions grants enhancement points.\n- Use these points in the main event page - Enhancement for initial enhancements.\n- Initial enhancements include: initial Star Coins, the number of talisman packs in the shop, the rarity of talisman packs in the shop, shop refresh price, talisman possession limit, and initial tile exchanges.\n- Initial enhancements can be reset anytime, returning all the points.\n- Applied enhancements will take effect at the start of your next game.\n\nDefault Talisman\n- Unlock condition: Clear Level 5-3.\n- You may select one Normal or Rare talisman from your Collection to set as your default. The default talisman is guaranteed to appear in the initial talisman selection of the game.\n- You can only set one default talisman.\n-After setting, this takes effect at the start of your next game.","Available for a long time","当前版本为测试版本，不代表最终品质，EID:{0}","此功能暂不可用","萬","億","兆","京","垓","秭","穰","溝","澗","正","載","極","M","B","T","Qa","Qi","Sx","Sp","Oc","No","Dc","Ud","Dd","Td","Qad","Qid","Sxd","Spd","Ocd","Nod","Vg","Uvg","Dvg","Tvg","Qavg","Qivg","Sxvg","Spvg","Ocvg","Novg","Tg","Utg","Dtg","Ttg","Qatg","Qitg","Sxtg","Sptg","Octg","Notg","Qag","Uqag","Dqag","Tqag","Qaqag","Qiqag","Sxqag","Spqag","Ocqag","Noqag","Qig","UQig","DQig","TQig","QaQig","QiQig","SxQig","SpQig","OcQig","NoQig","Sxg","USxg","DSxg","TSxg","QaSxg","QiSxg","SxSxg","SpSxg","OcSxg","NoSxg","Spg","USpg","DSpg","TSpg","QaSpg","QiSpg","SxSpg","SpSpg","OcSpg","NoSpg","Ocg","UOcg","DOcg","TOcg","QaOcg","QiOcg","SxOcg","SpOcg","OcOcg","NoOcg","Nog","UNog","DNog","TNog","QaNog","QiNog","SxNog","SpNog","OcNog","NoNog","Exit current mode and view this match\'s log?","Summer Limited Event - High Seas Hunt\nEvent Period: 8/19 - 9/9 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nThe legend of a lost treasure is reborn! A map has been found in the seas near One Han City.\nHeed the divine call and escape the noise of the world.\nJoin her crew, exploring the heart of these mysterious waters!\n\nDuring the event, complete missions to collect Compasses and earn exciting rewards, including limited Title, limited Tile Face, Event Illustration, Summon Scrolls, and more!","Tap to close","After the voting event ends, the Top 3 female character outfits and the Top 1 male character outfit will return for a limited time during the next event.\n\nIf server-wide voting progress reaches 100%, you will unlock a one-time opportunity to purchase any single outfit of your choice during the next event.\n- You can choose from all the outfits of regular characters.\n- This excludes collab outfits and does not contain special bonus decorations.\n- Players who did not participate in the vote will also unlock this opportunity.\n\nNow\'s your chance! Vote for the outfits you want to see return!","Rankings","Go Vote","Get Voting Tickets","Owned","The event has ended.","Who will it be?","Rankings update daily at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7).","Please wait for the next ranking update.","Displaying the Top 10 female outfits & Top 5 male outfits","Missions refresh daily at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7).","Use Voting Ticket x1 on {0}","If server-wide voting progress reaches 100%, you will unlock a one-time opportunity to purchase any single outfit of your choice in the upcoming event.\n- You can choose from all the outfits of regular characters.\n- This excludes collab outfits and does not contain special bonus decorations.\n- Players who did not participate in the vote will also unlock this opportunity.","*One-time purchase only.","--","Choose","Not yet selected","No outfits available for purchase","This character is hidden. Show them and go to the Dorm to change their outfit?","Season Mode","Individual","Team","Team Rankings","Individual Rankings","Team Name","Members","Team Matches Played","Total Team Score","View","Matches Played","Total Score","Player/Team","Freed Jyanshis","Total score:","No team members yet.","Collab Limited Event - Ichihime\'s Odd Jobs\nEvent Period: 10/21 - 11/11 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nA new Odd Jobs business is opening in One Han City, and its owner is none other than Ichihime!\nHelp her hire trustworthy employees to tackle all sorts of weird and whimsical requests!\n\nEvent Missions\n- Complete event missions to earn Taiyaki. Use Taiyaki in the Hiring Center to hire new employees.\n- You can also earn Taiyaki by playing in Ranked Match or the Upside Down event mode.\n-- Get 1st/2nd/3rd/4th place in 4-player mahjong: earn 8/6/4/2 Taiyaki\n-- Get 1st/2nd/3rd place in 3-player mahjong: earn 6/4/2 Taiyaki\n-- Winning (Baiman or above/Mangan or Haneman/below Mangan): earn 4/3/2 Taiyaki\n\nEvent Rewards\n- Complete a certain number of requests to claim various rewards, including limited Tile Back, limited Illustration, and Summon Scrolls!\n\nEvent Match\n- During the event, you can play in the brand-new match mode: Upside Down.\n- The fewer points you have, the higher the multiplier for your winning hands. Experience the thrill of a spectacular comeback, snatching victory from the jaws of defeat!\n- Please check the event match page for more details.\n\nHiring Center\n- Hiring: Hire employees to help complete requests.\n-- Each employee has three attributes (STR, SPD, LUK) and Stamina.\n-- Some employees have special abilities. Teaming them up may lead to much better outcomes.\n-- Use Taiyaki to hire employees or refresh the candidate list.\n- Roster: View information for all employees currently working at Ichihime\'s Odd Jobs.\n-- Use 1 Taiyaki to fully restore an employee\'s Stamina.\n-- At 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7) daily, all employees will have their Stamina fully restored.\n\nJob Requests\n- When you receive a request, you can assign 1-3 employees to complete it.\n- New requests will be unlocked gradually throughout the event.\n- Requests will check the combined STR, SPD, and LUK of the assigned employees. When their attributes meet all requirements, they can be sent out to complete the request.\n- If the total attributes of your assigned employees meet even higher requirements, they will complete the request with a Great Success.\n- Each assigned employee consumes 2 Stamina. A Great Success reduces this cost to 1 Stamina.\n- Completing certain requests will reward you with new employees.\n\nStory Review\n- Review event stories here. New chapters will be unlocked as the event progresses.","Experience the thrill of a spectacular comeback in the new 4-Player East special mode, Upside Down!\nEarn Taiyaki from Ranked Match or Upside Down. See event guide for more details.","Upside Down","Special Rules: Upside Down\nA special multiplier will be applied to winning hands, based on the player\'s current points.\n- 30,000 points or more: 1x\n- 20,000 to 29,900 points: 2x\n- 10,000 to 19,900 points: 3x\n- 9,900 points or less: 4x\n*The winning hand multiplier does not apply to total score, noten penalties, or Mangan at Draw.\n*Declaring Riichi costs 1,000 points, which may change your winning hand multiplier bracket.\n\nMatch Mode: Upside Down - 4-Player East\nRank Limit: None\nOrder Bonus: 1st +15, 2nd +5, 3rd -5, 4th -15\nEntry Limit: 5,000 Coppers\nExchange Rate: 1,000 Points = 100 Coppers\nEntry Fee: 1,000 Coppers\nMatches played in this mode are not ranked.\nCasual Chest Progress: 1st +260, 2nd +130, 3rd +95, 4th +60\n\nYou will receive Coppers if you finish with positive match points, or lose Coppers if your final score is in the negative.","Special Rules: Upside Down\nA special multiplier will be applied to winning hands, based on the player\'s current points.\n- 30,000 points or more: 1x\n- 20,000 to 29,900 points: 2x\n- 10,000 to 19,900 points: 3x\n- 9,900 points or less: 4x\n*The winning hand multiplier does not apply to total score, noten penalties, or Mangan at Draw.\n*Declaring Riichi costs 1,000 points, which may change your winning hand multiplier bracket.","Missions refresh daily at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7).","Story Review","Hiring Center","Hiring","Hire","There are no new candidates, nyaa","Roster","Job Requests","Client:","Complete the request to get Employee {0}","Requirements","Abilities","Assignment","Stamina (Desc)","STR (Desc)","SPD (Desc)","LUK (Desc)","Request in progress","No new requests today, nyaa","You\'ve finished all the requests, nyaa","Not enough Taiyaki, nyaa","Restore","About Request","There\'s nothing here, nyaa","Watch",":","None","Unable to Go","New employee!","Master, starting today, we\'re running the Odd Jobs in One Han City, nyaa! Our goal is to solve all the citizens\' problems, nyaa!","But there\'s no way just the two of us can handle everything, nyaa... Master, let\'s go check the [Hiring Center] and see if we can find any amazing helpers, nyaa!","Yay, Gin is willing to help, nyaa! Now that we have an employee, let\'s take a look at the requests, nyaa!","The first request is from... me, Ichihime, nyaa! Okay, Gin, I\'m leaving the prep work to you, nyaa!","The request was a purr-fect success! Here\'s some Taiyaki for everyone, nyaa!","Ichihime\'s Odd Jobs is now officially open, nyaa! Our next goal: expand our business and protect the peace of One Han City, nyaa!","Ichihime","Preparations for the Odd Jobs grand opening, nyaa.","No recommended candidates at the moment, nyaa.","Not enough Taiyaki! Earn more by completing event missions, playing Ranked matches, or playing the Upside Down event mode.","A Great Success costs 1 Stamina, while a regular Success costs 2 Stamina.","This employee is out of Stamina. Use Taiyaki to restore it.","Attribute requirements not met. Please add or change employees.","At 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7) daily, all employees will have their Stamina fully restored.","The Hibiki\'s Console event is LIVE NOW!\nEvent Period: 11/18 - 12/2 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nDuring the event, log in daily and complete event missions to earn Ammo.\nUse the joystick to move your fighter and fire Ammo to destroy enemies. Defeat them to earn rewards like the new Event Illustration, Sage\'s Bag, and more.\nJoin Hibiki Himekawa and aim to conquer every level!\n\n*Some enemies may require 2-3 shots to defeat.\n*Matches played against AI do not count towards event missions.\n*The event illustration may be added to Shop - Illustration in the future.\n*Event missions will be refreshed at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7) every day.\n*Matches that haven\'t finished before 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7) will not contribute to the previous day\'s mission progress.","Not enough Ammo. Complete missions to obtain more.","Not enough targets.","You have defeated all enemies!","Follow Dealer","Downloading resources... ({0}/{1})","Event - Super Mahjong Bingo\n\nDuring the event period, a new bingo card will be unlocked every day at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7).\nWin a hand in a match (excluding matches against AI) to mark off bingo spaces that correspond to the tiles in your winning hand.\nWhen all spaces in a horizontal, vertical, or diagonal line are marked off, you will earn the reward for that line.\n\nSpace Types\n- Free Space: Starts already marked off.\n- Man: Mark off by winning a hand that includes any Man tile.\n- Pin: Mark off by winning a hand that includes any Pin tile.\n- Sou: Mark off by winning a hand that includes any Sou tile.\n- Wind: Mark off by winning a hand that includes any Wind tile (East/South/West/North).\n- Dragon: Mark off by winning a hand that includes any Dragon tile (Red/Green/White).\n\n*Matches played against AI do not count towards event progress.\n*You can only mark off spaces on the bingo card currently displayed on the event page.","Complete the previous bingo card to unlock","12.7 - 12.16 1:59 P.M.(UTC-7)","Mark off bingo spaces by winning hands that contain the matching tiles (excluding matches against AI).","User Center","","","","CS Center","Winter Limited Event - Snowball Brawl\nEvent Period: 12/16 - 1/12 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nChaos descends on the winter dream – intruders have entered the snowy secret garden! Retreat is not an option for Lin Lang. Her weapons? Infinite resolve… and snowballs!\n\nDuring the event period, clear levels to claim various rewards, including Lobby BGM, Event Illustration, and Summon Scroll.\n\nAbout Snowballs\n- Aim High, Middle, or Low to deal 3, 2, or 1 damage respectively.\n- Throwing snowballs consumes energy and requires a short reload time.\n- Energy recovers automatically during battle.\n- Snowballs colliding on the same path will cancel each other out.\n- Snowballs have a chance to Crit, dealing bonus damage and becoming indestructible.\n\nAbout Training\n- Complete missions to get Dragon\'s Pearls.\n- Use them to boost Lin Lang\'s stats and upgrade her snowballs.\n\nLin Lang\'s Tips\n- The key to victory lies in countering enemy moves and breaking through their defenses.\n- Don\'t worry – no one actually gets hurt in this snowball fight!","Level {0}","{0} levels left","All Cleared","Loop {0}: Level ∞ {1}","Claim","Return","Continue","Enter the next level in {0}s","I need to get stronger first...","Go Upgrade","Try Again","Leaving now will restart the level. Are you sure?","Leave","Resume","Lin Lang","Upgrade","Snowball 1","Snowball 2","Snowball 3","Clear {0} to Unlock","Per Throw","Energy Cost","Reload Time","Health","Level reward claimed","Clear {0} to claim","Level reward unlocked","All levels cleared! You can continue playing, but you will no longer receive rewards. Would you like to enter the next Loop?","Do you want to reset enhancements? After the reset, all enhanced abilities are set to Lv1, and all enhancement points are returned.","Matchmaking rules have been changed by the admin.","Enabled","Disabled","VSync","Mia\'s Channel","[1.13 - 1.27 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)]","Mia\'s Channel – LIVE NOW!\nEvent Period: 1/13 - 1/27 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nDuring the event, log in daily and complete missions to obtain event items.\nGift these items in Mia\'s stream to interact with her and increase her channel\'s Popularity.\nWhen the channel\'s Popularity reaches certain milestones, you can claim Fan Rewards, including Event Illustration, Sage\'s Bags, and more!\n\n*Matches played against AI do not count toward event missions.\n*The event illustration may be added to Shop - Illustration in the future.","Mia Shinohara","Current Popularity","Reserve Match","Reserved Start Time","Match starts in {0}","---","Please confirm you are Ready","Waiting for other players...","Match starts in {0} days","Use all available attempts to flip missions in order?","All missions have been revealed.","Please select a pair of Rate Up characters. During the event, you can change your selection at any time!","Select Rate Up Pair","Owned","You have obtained both of the current Rate Up characters! You can still select another pair for Rate Up!","You already own all selectable regular characters in Sakura Path.","You already own all selectable regular characters in Bamboo Path.","Selection can be changed at any time","{0} & {1}","Owned","2/10 - 3/6 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)","Spring Festival Event - Wishes Unbridled\n\nEvent Period: 2/10 - 3/6 1:59 P.M. (UTC-7)\n\nTo gather wishes and hone her skills, Chi Lin, Lady of the Horse Palace, is dashing through the streets of One Han City to deliver delicious treats!\nClear mahjong obstacles along the way to collect Chi Lin\'s favorite Carrots and boost her Gallop Power, carrying her message as far as you can!\nDuring the event, complete missions and play the minigame to earn various rewards, including Spring Festival Emotes, exclusive Tablecloth, Event Illustration, and Summon Scrolls!\n\nControls\n- Chi Lin automatically runs to the right.\n- Tap the [Up/Down Arrows] on the right side of the screen, or press [W/S] / [↑/↓] on your keyboard to move up and down.\n\nGame Rules\n- Hit mahjong tiles to collect them in Chi Lin\'s bag. It can hold a maximum of 7 tiles.\n- Forming a sequence or triplet automatically clears the tiles and grants Carrots.\n- The game ends if the bag is full and no new meld can be made, or when the timer reaches 0.\n- Collect special items along the way to earn bonus Carrots or extend game time.\n- Accumulate Carrots and increase Gallop Power from each run to unlock event rewards.\n\nLucky Tiles and Gallop Time\n- At the start of the game, 3 different tiles are randomly designated as [Lucky Tiles], highlighted in yellow.\n- Clearing a meld that contains a Lucky Tile grants bonus Carrots and adds extra time.\n- Clear all 3 Lucky Tiles to trigger Gallop Time! During this mode, all upcoming tiles become Lucky Tiles – the perfect chance to harvest a ton of Carrots!","Total Collected","Best Time","Best Distance","Most Collected in Single Run","Gallop Power","{0}/{1}","Lucky Tiles","Results","Time","Distance","Collected","Run Again","Confirm","Incomplete","Completed","Refreshes daily at 2:00 P.M. (UTC-7)","Paused","Quit","Restart","Continue","Unlocks at Max Gallop Power","An unexpected error occurred, please re-enter the game."}return a